60 Address AddressOf(const StackHandler* handler) {
61  Address raw = handler->address();
62 #ifdef V8_USE_ADDRESS_SANITIZER
63  // ASan puts C++-allocated StackHandler markers onto its fake stack.
64  // We work around that by storing the real stack address in the "padding"
65  // field. StackHandlers allocated from generated code have 0 as padding.
66  Address padding =
67  base::Memory<Address>(raw + StackHandlerConstants::kPaddingOffset);
68  if (padding != 0) return padding;
69 #endif
70  return raw;
71 }

75 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
76 bool IsWasmToJsWrapperCSA(Address pc) {
77  // The WasmToJsWrapper can also be called from the embedded data directly.
78  size_t builtin_size =
79  EmbeddedData::FromBlob().InstructionSizeOf(Builtin::kWasmToJsWrapperCSA);
80  Address wrapper_addr =
81  Builtins::EmbeddedEntryOf(Builtin::kWasmToJsWrapperCSA);
82  if (pc >= wrapper_addr && pc < wrapper_addr + builtin_size) {
83  return true;
84  }
85 
86  return false;
87 }
88 #endif

90 // Iterator that supports traversing the stack handlers of a
91 // particular frame. Needs to know the top of the handler chain.
92 class StackHandlerIterator {
93  public:
94  StackHandlerIterator(const StackFrame* frame, StackHandler* handler)
95  : limit_(frame->fp()), handler_(handler) {
96 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
97 #if !V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE && !USE_SIMULATOR
98  // Make sure the handler has already been unwound to this frame. With stack
99  // switching this is not equivalent to the inequality below, because the
100  // frame and the handler could be in different stacks.
101  DCHECK_IMPLIES(frame->isolate()->wasm_stacks().empty(),
102  frame->InFastCCall() || frame->sp() <= AddressOf(handler));
103 #endif // !V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE || !USE_SIMULATOR
104 
105  // For CWasmEntry frames, the handler was registered by the last C++
106  // frame (Execution::CallWasm), so even though its address is already
107  // beyond the limit, we know we always want to unwind one handler.
108  if (frame->is_c_wasm_entry()) {
109  handler_ = handler_->next();
110 #if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
111  // Do the same for GenericWasmToJsInterpreterWrapper frames.
112  } else if (v8_flags.wasm_jitless && frame->is_wasm_to_js()) {
113  handler_ = handler_->next();
114 #ifdef USE_SIMULATOR
115  // If we are running in the simulator, the handler_ address here will
116  // refer to the 'actual' stack, not to the 'simulated' stack, so we need
117  // to fix 'limit_' to make sure that the StackHandlerIterator won't skip
118  // any handler.
119  limit_ = 0;
120 #endif // USE_SIMULATOR
121 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
122  }
123 #else
124  // Make sure the handler has already been unwound to this frame.
125  DCHECK_LE(frame->sp(), AddressOf(handler));
126 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
127  }
128 
129  StackHandler* handler() const { return handler_; }
130 
131  bool done() { return handler_ == nullptr || AddressOf(handler_) > limit_; }
132  void Advance() {
133  DCHECK(!done());
134  handler_ = handler_->next();
135  }
136 
137  private:
138 #if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE && USE_SIMULATOR
139  Address limit_;
140 #else
141  const Address limit_;
142 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE && USE_SIMULATOR
143 
144  StackHandler* handler_;
145 };

175 
176 void StackFrameIterator::Advance() {
177  DCHECK(!done());
178  // Compute the state of the calling frame before restoring
179  // callee-saved registers and unwinding handlers. This allows the
180  // frame code that computes the caller state to access the top
181  // handler and the value of any callee-saved register if needed.
182  StackFrame::State state;
183  StackFrame::Type type;
184 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
185  if (frame_->type() == StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH &&
186  Memory<Address>(frame_->fp() +
187  StackSwitchFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset) ==
188  kNullAddress &&
189  !first_stack_only_) {
190  // Handle stack switches here.
191  // Note: both the "callee" frame (outermost frame of the child stack) and
192  // the "caller" frame (top frame of the parent stack) have frame type
193  // STACK_SWITCH. We use the caller FP to distinguish them: the callee frame
194  // does not have a caller fp.
195  wasm_stack_ = wasm_stack()->jmpbuf()->parent;
196  CHECK_NOT_NULL(wasm_stack_);
197  CHECK_EQ(wasm_stack_->jmpbuf()->state, wasm::JumpBuffer::Inactive);
198  StackSwitchFrame::GetStateForJumpBuffer(wasm_stack_->jmpbuf(), &state);
199  SetNewFrame(StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH, &state);
200  return;
201  }
202 #endif
203  type = frame_->GetCallerState(&state);
204 
205  // {StackHandlerIterator} assumes that frame pointers strictly go from lower
206  // to higher addresses as we iterate the stack. This breaks with
207  // stack-switching, so only unwind the stack handlers for frames that are
208  // known to use them.
209  if (frame_->type() == StackFrame::ENTRY ||
210  frame_->type() == StackFrame::CONSTRUCT_ENTRY
211 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
212  || frame_->type() == StackFrame::C_WASM_ENTRY
213 #endif
214  ) {
215  StackHandlerIterator it(frame_, handler_);
216  while (!it.done()) it.Advance();
217  handler_ = it.handler();
218  }
219 
220  // Advance to the calling frame.
221  SetNewFrame(type, &state);
222  // When we're done iterating over the stack frames, the handler
223  // chain must have been completely unwound. Except if we are only iterating
224  // the first stack of the chain for wasm stack-switching.
225 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
226  DCHECK_IMPLIES(done() && !first_stack_only_, handler_ == nullptr);
227 #else
228  DCHECK_IMPLIES(done(), handler_ == nullptr);
229 #endif
230 }
231 
232 StackFrame* StackFrameIterator::Reframe() {
233  StackFrame::State state = frame_->state_;
234  StackFrame::Type type = ComputeStackFrameType(&state);
235  SetNewFrame(type, &state);
236  return frame();
237 }
238 
239 namespace {
240 StackFrame::Type GetStateForFastCCallCallerFP(Isolate* isolate, Address fp,
241  Address pc, Address pc_address,
242  StackFrame::State* state) {
243  // 'Fast C calls' are a special type of C call where we call directly from
244  // JS to C without an exit frame in between. The CEntryStub is responsible
245  // for setting Isolate::c_entry_fp, meaning that it won't be set for fast C
246  // calls. To keep the stack iterable, we store the FP and PC of the caller
247  // of the fast C call on the isolate. This is guaranteed to be the topmost
248  // JS frame, because fast C calls cannot call back into JS. We start
249  // iterating the stack from this topmost JS frame.
250  DCHECK_NE(kNullAddress, pc);
251  state->fp = fp;
252  state->sp = kNullAddress;
253  state->pc_address = reinterpret_cast<Address*>(pc_address);
254  state->callee_pc = kNullAddress;
255  state->constant_pool_address = nullptr;
256 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
257  if (wasm::WasmCode* code =
258  wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCode(isolate, pc)) {
259  if (code->kind() == wasm::WasmCode::kWasmToJsWrapper) {
260  return StackFrame::WASM_TO_JS;
261  }
262  DCHECK_EQ(code->kind(), wasm::WasmCode::kWasmFunction);
263  return StackFrame::WASM;
264  }
265 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
266  return StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS;
267 }
268 } // namespace
269 
270 void StackFrameIterator::Reset(ThreadLocalTop* top) {
271  StackFrame::State state;
272  StackFrame::Type type;
273 
274  const Address fast_c_call_caller_fp =
275  isolate_->isolate_data()->fast_c_call_caller_fp();
276  if (fast_c_call_caller_fp != kNullAddress) {
277  const Address caller_pc = isolate_->isolate_data()->fast_c_call_caller_pc();
278  const Address caller_pc_address =
279  isolate_->isolate_data()->fast_c_call_caller_pc_address();
280  type = GetStateForFastCCallCallerFP(isolate_, fast_c_call_caller_fp,
281  caller_pc, caller_pc_address, &state);
282  } else {
283  type = ExitFrame::GetStateForFramePointer(Isolate::c_entry_fp(top), &state);
284  }
285 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
286  wasm_stack_ = isolate_->isolate_data()->active_stack();
287 #endif
288  handler_ = StackHandler::FromAddress(Isolate::handler(top));
289  SetNewFrame(type, &state);
290 }
291 
292 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
293 void StackFrameIterator::Reset(ThreadLocalTop* top, wasm::StackMemory* stack) {
294  if (stack->jmpbuf()->state == wasm::JumpBuffer::Retired) {
295  return;
296  }
297  StackFrame::State state;
298  StackSwitchFrame::GetStateForJumpBuffer(stack->jmpbuf(), &state);
299  handler_ = StackHandler::FromAddress(Isolate::handler(top));
300  wasm_stack_ = stack;
301  SetNewFrame(StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH, &state);
302 }
303 #endif
304 
305 void StackFrameIteratorBase::SetNewFrame(StackFrame::Type type,
306  StackFrame::State* state) {
307  SetNewFrame(type);
308  DCHECK_EQ(!frame_, type == StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
309  if (frame_) frame_->state_ = *state;
310 }
311 
312 void StackFrameIteratorBase::SetNewFrame(StackFrame::Type type) {
313  switch (type) {
314 #define FRAME_TYPE_CASE(type, class) \
315  case StackFrame::type: \
316  frame_ = new (&class##_) class(this); \
317  return;
318  STACK_FRAME_TYPE_LIST(FRAME_TYPE_CASE)
319 #undef FRAME_TYPE_CASE
320 
321  case StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE:
322  // We don't expect to see NUMBER_OF_TYPES or MANUAL, but stay robust against
323  // them rather than being UNREACHABLE in case stack frame iteration gets
324  // wonky.
325  case StackFrame::NUMBER_OF_TYPES:
326  case StackFrame::MANUAL:
327  break;
328  }
329  frame_ = nullptr;
330 }

341 void ConstructFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
342  // The frame contains the actual argument count (intptr) that should not
343  // be visited.
344  FullObjectSlot argc(
345  &Memory<Address>(fp() + ConstructFrameConstants::kLengthOffset));
346  const int last_object_offset = ConstructFrameConstants::kLastObjectOffset;
347  FullObjectSlot base(&Memory<Address>(sp()));
348  FullObjectSlot limit(&Memory<Address>(fp() + last_object_offset) + 1);
349  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, base, argc);
350  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, argc + 1, limit);
351  IteratePc(v, constant_pool_address(), GcSafeLookupCode());
352 }

381 int DebuggableStackFrameIterator::FrameFunctionCount() const {
382  DCHECK(!done());
383  if (!iterator_.frame()->is_optimized_js()) return 1;
384  std::vector<Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo>> infos;
385  TurbofanJSFrame::cast(iterator_.frame())->GetFunctions(&infos);
386  return static_cast<int>(infos.size());
387 }
388 
389 FrameSummary DebuggableStackFrameIterator::GetTopValidFrame() const {
390  DCHECK(!done());
391  // Like FrameSummary::GetTop, but additionally observes
392  // DebuggableStackFrameIterator filtering semantics.
393  FrameSummaries summaries = frame()->Summarize();
394  if (is_javascript()) {
395  for (int i = summaries.size() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
396  const FrameSummary& summary = summaries.frames[i];
397  if (summary.is_subject_to_debugging()) {
398  return summary;
399  }
400  }
401  UNREACHABLE();
402  }
403 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
404  if (is_wasm()) return summaries.frames.back();
405 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
406  UNREACHABLE();
407 }

409 // static
410 bool DebuggableStackFrameIterator::IsValidFrame(StackFrame* frame) {
411  if (frame->is_javascript()) {
412  Tagged<JSFunction> function =
413  static_cast<JavaScriptFrame*>(frame)->function();
414  return function->shared()->IsSubjectToDebugging();
415  }
416 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
417  if (frame->is_wasm()) return true;
418 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
419  return false;
420 }

424 namespace {
425 
426 std::optional<bool> IsInterpreterFramePc(Isolate* isolate, Address pc,
427  StackFrame::State* state) {
428  Builtin builtin = OffHeapInstructionStream::TryLookupCode(isolate, pc);
429  if (builtin != Builtin::kNoBuiltinId &&
430  (builtin == Builtin::kInterpreterEntryTrampoline ||
431  builtin == Builtin::kInterpreterEnterAtBytecode ||
432  builtin == Builtin::kInterpreterEnterAtNextBytecode)) {
433  return true;
434  } else if (isolate->interpreted_frames_native_stack()) {
435  intptr_t marker = Memory<intptr_t>(
436  state->fp + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset);
437  MSAN_MEMORY_IS_INITIALIZED(
438  state->fp + StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset,
439  kSystemPointerSize);
440  Tagged<Object> maybe_function = Tagged<Object>(
441  Memory<Address>(state->fp + StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset));
442  // There's no need to run a full ContainsSlow if we know the frame can't be
443  // an InterpretedFrame, so we do these fast checks first
444  if (StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker) || IsSmi(maybe_function)) {
445  return false;
446  } else if (!isolate->heap()->InSpaceSlow(pc, CODE_SPACE)) {
447  return false;
448  }
449  if (!ThreadIsolation::CanLookupStartOfJitAllocationAt(pc)) {
450  return {};
451  }
452  Tagged<Code> interpreter_entry_trampoline =
453  isolate->heap()->FindCodeForInnerPointer(pc);
454  return interpreter_entry_trampoline->is_interpreter_trampoline_builtin();
455  } else {
456  return false;
457  }
458 }

462 bool StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::IsNoFrameBytecodeHandlerPc(
463  Isolate* isolate, Address pc, Address fp) const {
464  EmbeddedData d = EmbeddedData::FromBlob(isolate);
465  if (pc < d.InstructionStartOfBytecodeHandlers() ||
466  pc >= d.InstructionEndOfBytecodeHandlers()) {
467  return false;
468  }
469 
470  Address frame_type_address =
471  fp + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset;
472  if (!IsValidStackAddress(frame_type_address)) {
473  return false;
474  }
475 
476  // Check if top stack frame is a bytecode handler stub frame.
477  MSAN_MEMORY_IS_INITIALIZED(frame_type_address, kSystemPointerSize);
478  intptr_t marker = Memory<intptr_t>(frame_type_address);
479  if (StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker) &&
480  StackFrame::MarkerToType(marker) == StackFrame::STUB) {
481  // Bytecode handler built a frame.
482  return false;
483  }
484  return true;
485 }
486 
487 StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::StackFrameIteratorForProfiler(
488  Isolate* isolate, Address pc, Address fp, Address sp, Address lr,
489  Address js_entry_sp)
490  : StackFrameIteratorBase(isolate),
491  low_bound_(sp),
492  high_bound_(js_entry_sp),
493  top_frame_type_(StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE),
494  external_callback_scope_(isolate->external_callback_scope()),
495  top_link_register_(lr)
496 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
497  ,
498  wasm_stacks_(isolate->wasm_stacks())
499 #endif
500 {
501  if (!isolate->isolate_data()->stack_is_iterable()) {
502  // The stack is not iterable in a short time interval during deoptimization.
503  // See also: ExternalReference::stack_is_iterable_address.
504  DCHECK(done());
505  return;
506  }
507 
508  // For Advance below, we need frame_ to be set; and that only happens if the
509  // type is not NO_FRAME_TYPE.
510  // TODO(jgruber): Clean this up.
511  static constexpr StackFrame::Type kTypeForAdvance = StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS;
512 
513  StackFrame::State state;
514  state.is_profiler_entry_frame = true;
515  StackFrame::Type type;
516  ThreadLocalTop* const top = isolate->thread_local_top();
517  bool advance_frame = true;
518  const Address fast_c_fp = isolate->isolate_data()->fast_c_call_caller_fp();
519  if (fast_c_fp != kNullAddress) {
520  // 'Fast C calls' are a special type of C call where we call directly from
521  // JS to C without an exit frame in between. The CEntryStub is responsible
522  // for setting Isolate::c_entry_fp, meaning that it won't be set for fast C
523  // calls. To keep the stack iterable, we store the FP and PC of the caller
524  // of the fast C call on the isolate. This is guaranteed to be the topmost
525  // JS frame, because fast C calls cannot call back into JS. We start
526  // iterating the stack from this topmost JS frame.
527  DCHECK_NE(kNullAddress, isolate->isolate_data()->fast_c_call_caller_pc());
528  state.fp = fast_c_fp;
529  state.sp = sp;
530  state.pc_address = reinterpret_cast<Address*>(
531  isolate->isolate_data()->fast_c_call_caller_pc_address());
532 
533  // ComputeStackFrameType will read both kContextOffset and
534  // kFunctionOffset, we check only that kFunctionOffset is within the stack
535  // bounds and do a compile time check that kContextOffset slot is pushed on
536  // the stack before kFunctionOffset.
537  static_assert(StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset <
538  StandardFrameConstants::kContextOffset);
539  if (IsValidStackAddress(state.fp +
540  StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset)) {
541  type = ComputeStackFrameType(&state);
542  if (IsValidFrameType(type)) {
543  top_frame_type_ = type;
544  advance_frame = false;
545  }
546  } else {
547  // Cannot determine the actual type; the frame will be skipped below.
548  type = kTypeForAdvance;
549  }
550  } else if (IsValidTop(top)) {
551  type = ExitFrame::GetStateForFramePointer(Isolate::c_entry_fp(top), &state);
552  top_frame_type_ = type;
553  } else if (IsValidStackAddress(fp)) {
554  DCHECK_NE(fp, kNullAddress);
555  state.fp = fp;
556  state.sp = sp;
557  state.pc_address =
558  StackFrame::ResolveReturnAddressLocation(reinterpret_cast<Address*>(
559  fp + StandardFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset));
560 
561  bool can_lookup_frame_type =
562  // Ensure frame structure is not broken, otherwise it doesn't make
563  // sense to try to detect a frame type.
564  (sp < fp) &&
565  // Ensure there is a context/frame type value in the frame.
566  (fp - sp) >= TypedFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp;
567 
568  // If the current PC is in a bytecode handler, the top stack frame isn't
569  // the bytecode handler's frame and the top of stack or link register is a
570  // return address into the interpreter entry trampoline, then we are likely
571  // in a bytecode handler with elided frame. In that case, set the PC
572  // properly and make sure we do not drop the frame.
573  bool is_no_frame_bytecode_handler = false;
574  if (can_lookup_frame_type && IsNoFrameBytecodeHandlerPc(isolate, pc, fp)) {
575  Address* top_location = nullptr;
576  if (top_link_register_) {
577  top_location = &top_link_register_;
578  } else if (IsValidStackAddress(sp)) {
579  MSAN_MEMORY_IS_INITIALIZED(sp, kSystemPointerSize);
580  top_location = reinterpret_cast<Address*>(sp);
581  }
582 
583  std::optional<bool> is_interpreter_frame_pc =
584  IsInterpreterFramePc(isolate, *top_location, &state);
585  // Since we're in a signal handler, the pc lookup might not be possible
586  // since the required locks are taken by the same thread.
587  if (!is_interpreter_frame_pc.has_value()) {
588  can_lookup_frame_type = false;
589  } else if (is_interpreter_frame_pc.value()) {
590  state.pc_address = top_location;
591  is_no_frame_bytecode_handler = true;
592  advance_frame = false;
593  }
594  }
595 
596  // ComputeStackFrameType will read both kContextOffset and
597  // kFunctionOffset, we check only that kFunctionOffset is within the stack
598  // bounds and do a compile time check that kContextOffset slot is pushed on
599  // the stack before kFunctionOffset.
600  static_assert(StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset <
601  StandardFrameConstants::kContextOffset);
602  Address function_slot = fp + StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset;
603  if (!can_lookup_frame_type) {
604  type = StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE;
605  } else if (IsValidStackAddress(function_slot)) {
606  if (is_no_frame_bytecode_handler) {
607  type = StackFrame::INTERPRETED;
608  } else {
609  type = ComputeStackFrameType(&state);
610  }
611  top_frame_type_ = type;
612  } else {
613  // Cannot determine the actual type; the frame will be skipped below.
614  type = kTypeForAdvance;
615  }
616  } else {
617  // Not iterable.
618  DCHECK(done());
619  return;
620  }
621 
622  SetNewFrame(type, &state);
623  if (advance_frame && !done()) {
624  Advance();
625  }
626 }
627 
628 bool StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::IsValidTop(ThreadLocalTop* top) const {
629  Address c_entry_fp = Isolate::c_entry_fp(top);
630  if (!IsValidExitFrame(c_entry_fp)) return false;
631  // There should be at least one JS_ENTRY stack handler.
632  Address handler = Isolate::handler(top);
633  return handler != kNullAddress;
634 }
635 
636 void StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::AdvanceOneFrame() {
637  DCHECK(!done());
638  StackFrame* last_frame = frame_;
639  Address last_sp = last_frame->sp(), last_fp = last_frame->fp();
640 
641  // Before advancing to the next stack frame, perform pointer validity tests.
642  if (!IsValidState(last_frame->state_) ||
643  !HasValidExitIfEntryFrame(last_frame)) {
644  frame_ = nullptr;
645  return;
646  }
647 
648  // Advance to the previous frame, and perform pointer validity tests there
649  // too.
650  StackFrame::State state;
651  last_frame->ComputeCallerState(&state);
652  if (!IsValidState(state)) {
653  frame_ = nullptr;
654  return;
655  }
656 
657  StackFrame::Type type = ComputeStackFrameType(&state);
658  SetNewFrame(type, &state);
659  if (!frame_) return;
660 
661  // Check that we have actually moved to the previous frame in the stack.
662  if (frame_->sp() <= last_sp || frame_->fp() <= last_fp) {
663  frame_ = nullptr;
664  }
665 }
666 
667 bool StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::IsValidState(
668  const StackFrame::State& state) const {
669  return IsValidStackAddress(state.sp) && IsValidStackAddress(state.fp);
670 }
671 
672 bool StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::HasValidExitIfEntryFrame(
673  const StackFrame* frame) const {
674  if (!frame->is_entry() && !frame->is_construct_entry()) return true;
675 
676  // See EntryFrame::GetCallerState. It computes the caller FP address
677  // and calls ExitFrame::GetStateForFramePointer on it. We need to be
678  // sure that caller FP address is valid.
679  Address next_exit_frame_fp_address =
680  frame->fp() + EntryFrameConstants::kNextExitFrameFPOffset;
681  // Profiling tick might be triggered in the middle of JSEntry builtin
682  // before the next_exit_frame_fp value is initialized. IsValidExitFrame()
683  // is able to deal with such a case, so just suppress the MSan warning.
684  MSAN_MEMORY_IS_INITIALIZED(next_exit_frame_fp_address, kSystemPointerSize);
685  Address next_exit_frame_fp = Memory<Address>(next_exit_frame_fp_address);
686  return IsValidExitFrame(next_exit_frame_fp);
687 }
688 
689 bool StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::IsValidExitFrame(Address fp) const {
690  if (!IsAligned(fp, kSystemPointerSize)) return false;
691  if (!IsValidStackAddress(fp)) return false;
692  Address sp = ExitFrame::ComputeStackPointer(fp);
693  if (!IsValidStackAddress(sp)) return false;
694  StackFrame::State state;
695  ExitFrame::FillState(fp, sp, &state);
696  MSAN_MEMORY_IS_INITIALIZED(state.pc_address, sizeof(state.pc_address));
697  return *state.pc_address != kNullAddress;
698 }
699 
700 void StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::Advance() {
701  while (true) {
702  AdvanceOneFrame();
703  if (done()) break;
704  ExternalCallbackScope* last_callback_scope = nullptr;
705  while (external_callback_scope_ != nullptr &&
706  external_callback_scope_->JSStackComparableAddress() <
707  frame_->fp()) {
708  // As long as the setup of a frame is not atomic, we may happen to be
709  // in an interval where an ExternalCallbackScope is already created,
710  // but the frame is not yet entered. So we are actually observing
711  // the previous frame.
712  // Skip all the ExternalCallbackScope's that are below the current fp.
713  last_callback_scope = external_callback_scope_;
714  external_callback_scope_ = external_callback_scope_->previous();
715  }
716  if (frame_->is_javascript()) break;
717 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
718  if (frame_->is_wasm() || frame_->is_wasm_to_js() ||
719  frame_->is_js_to_wasm()) {
720  break;
721  }
722 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
723  if (frame_->is_exit() || frame_->is_builtin_exit() ||
724  frame_->is_api_accessor_exit() || frame_->is_api_callback_exit()) {
725  // Some of the EXIT frames may have ExternalCallbackScope allocated on
726  // top of them. In that case the scope corresponds to the first EXIT
727  // frame beneath it. There may be other EXIT frames on top of the
728  // ExternalCallbackScope, just skip them as we cannot collect any useful
729  // information about them.
730  if (last_callback_scope) {
731  frame_->state_.pc_address =
732  last_callback_scope->callback_entrypoint_address();
733  }
734  break;
735  }
736  }
737 }

743  : StackFrameIteratorForProfiler(isolate, pc, fp, sp, lr, js_entry_sp) {}
744 
745 void StackFrameIteratorForProfilerForTesting::Advance() {
746  StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::Advance();
747 }

782 
783 void StackFrame::IteratePc(RootVisitor* v, Address* constant_pool_address,
784  Tagged<GcSafeCode> holder) const {
785  const Address old_pc = maybe_unauthenticated_pc();
786  DCHECK_GE(old_pc, holder->InstructionStart(isolate(), old_pc));
787  DCHECK_LT(old_pc, holder->InstructionEnd(isolate(), old_pc));
788 
789  // Keep the old pc offset before visiting the code since we need it to
790  // calculate the new pc after a potential InstructionStream move.
791  const uintptr_t pc_offset_from_start = old_pc - holder->instruction_start();
792 
793  // Visit.
794  Tagged<GcSafeCode> visited_holder = holder;
795  PtrComprCageBase code_cage_base{isolate()->code_cage_base()};
796  const Tagged<Object> old_istream =
797  holder->raw_instruction_stream(code_cage_base);
798  Tagged<Object> visited_istream = old_istream;
799  v->VisitRunningCode(FullObjectSlot{&visited_holder},
800  FullObjectSlot{&visited_istream});
801  if (visited_istream == old_istream) {
802  // Note this covers two important cases:
803  // 1. the associated InstructionStream object did not move, and
804  // 2. `holder` is an embedded builtin and has no InstructionStream.
805  return;
806  }
807 
808  DCHECK(visited_holder->has_instruction_stream());
809  // We can only relocate the InstructionStream object when we are able to patch
810  // the return address. We only know the location of the return address if the
811  // stack pointer is known. This means we cannot relocate InstructionStreams
812  // for fast c calls.
813  DCHECK(!InFastCCall());
814  // Currently we turn off code space compaction fully when performing a GC in a
815  // fast C call.
816  DCHECK(!isolate()->InFastCCall());
817 
818  Tagged<InstructionStream> istream =
819  GCSafeCast<InstructionStream>(visited_istream, isolate()->heap());
820  const Address new_pc = istream->instruction_start() + pc_offset_from_start;
821  // TODO(v8:10026): avoid replacing a signed pointer.
822  PointerAuthentication::ReplacePC(pc_address(), new_pc, kSystemPointerSize);
823  if (V8_EMBEDDED_CONSTANT_POOL_BOOL && constant_pool_address != nullptr) {
824  *constant_pool_address = istream->constant_pool();
825  }
826 }

836 StackFrame::Type ComputeBuiltinFrameType(Tagged<GcSafeCode> code) {
837  if (code->is_interpreter_trampoline_builtin() ||
838  code->is_baseline_trampoline_builtin()) {
839  // Frames for baseline entry trampolines on the stack are still interpreted
840  // frames.
841  return StackFrame::INTERPRETED;
842  } else if (code->is_baseline_leave_frame_builtin()) {
843  return StackFrame::BASELINE;
844  } else if (code->is_turbofanned()) {
845  // TODO(bmeurer): We treat frames for BUILTIN Code objects as
846  // OptimizedJSFrame for now (all the builtins with JavaScript linkage are
847  // actually generated with TurboFan currently, so this is sound).
848  return StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS;
849  }
850  return StackFrame::BUILTIN;
851 }
852 
853 StackFrame::Type SafeStackFrameType(StackFrame::Type candidate) {
854  DCHECK_LE(static_cast<uintptr_t>(candidate), StackFrame::NUMBER_OF_TYPES);
855  switch (candidate) {
856  case StackFrame::API_ACCESSOR_EXIT:
857  case StackFrame::API_CALLBACK_EXIT:
858  case StackFrame::BUILTIN_CONTINUATION:
859  case StackFrame::BUILTIN_EXIT:
860  case StackFrame::CONSTRUCT:
861  case StackFrame::FAST_CONSTRUCT:
862  case StackFrame::CONSTRUCT_ENTRY:
863  case StackFrame::ENTRY:
864  case StackFrame::EXIT:
865  case StackFrame::INTERNAL:
866  case StackFrame::IRREGEXP:
867  case StackFrame::JAVASCRIPT_BUILTIN_CONTINUATION:
868  case StackFrame::JAVASCRIPT_BUILTIN_CONTINUATION_WITH_CATCH:
869  case StackFrame::STUB:
870  return candidate;
871 
872 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
873  case StackFrame::JS_TO_WASM:
874  case StackFrame::STACK_SWITCH:
875  case StackFrame::WASM:
876  case StackFrame::WASM_DEBUG_BREAK:
877  case StackFrame::WASM_EXIT:
878  case StackFrame::WASM_LIFTOFF_SETUP:
879  case StackFrame::WASM_TO_JS:
880  case StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START:
881 #if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
882  case StackFrame::C_WASM_ENTRY:
883  case StackFrame::WASM_INTERPRETER_ENTRY:
884 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
885  return candidate;
886 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
887 
888  // Any other marker value is likely to be a bogus stack frame when being
889  // called from the profiler (in particular, JavaScript frames, including
890  // interpreted frames, should never have a StackFrame::Type marker).
891  // Consider these frames "native".
892  // TODO(jgruber): For the StackFrameIterator, I'm not sure this fallback
893  // makes sense. Shouldn't we know how to handle all frames we encounter
894  // there?
895  case StackFrame::BASELINE:
896  case StackFrame::BUILTIN:
897  case StackFrame::INTERPRETED:
898  case StackFrame::MAGLEV:
899  case StackFrame::MANUAL:
900  case StackFrame::NATIVE:
901  case StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE:
902  case StackFrame::NUMBER_OF_TYPES:
903  case StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS:
904  case StackFrame::TURBOFAN_STUB_WITH_CONTEXT:
905 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY && !V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
906  case StackFrame::C_WASM_ENTRY:
907 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY && !V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
908  return StackFrame::NATIVE;
909  }
910  UNREACHABLE();
911 }
912 
913 } // namespace
914 
915 StackFrame::Type StackFrameIterator::ComputeStackFrameType(
916  StackFrame::State* state) const {
917 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
918  if (state->fp == kNullAddress && first_stack_only_) {
919  DCHECK(!isolate_->wasm_stacks().empty()); // I.e., JSPI active
920  return StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE;
921  }
922 #endif
923 
924  const Address pc = StackFrame::ReadPC(state->pc_address);
925 
926 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
927  // If the {pc} does not point into WebAssembly code we can rely on the
928  // returned {wasm_code} to be null and fall back to {GetContainingCode}.
929  if (wasm::WasmCode* wasm_code =
930  wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCode(isolate(), pc)) {
931  switch (wasm_code->kind()) {
932  case wasm::WasmCode::kWasmFunction:
933  return StackFrame::WASM;
934  case wasm::WasmCode::kWasmToCapiWrapper:
935  return StackFrame::WASM_EXIT;
936  case wasm::WasmCode::kWasmToJsWrapper:
937  return StackFrame::WASM_TO_JS;
938 #if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
939  case wasm::WasmCode::kInterpreterEntry:
940  return StackFrame::WASM_INTERPRETER_ENTRY;
941 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
942  default:
943  UNREACHABLE();
944  }
945  }
946 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
947 
948  // Look up the code object to figure out the type of the stack frame.
949  std::optional<Tagged<GcSafeCode>> lookup_result =
950  GetContainingCode(isolate(), pc);
951  if (!lookup_result.has_value()) return StackFrame::NATIVE;
952 
953  MSAN_MEMORY_IS_INITIALIZED(
954  state->fp + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset,
955  kSystemPointerSize);
956  const intptr_t marker = Memory<intptr_t>(
957  state->fp + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset);
958  switch (lookup_result.value()->kind()) {
959  case CodeKind::BUILTIN:
960  case CodeKind::FOR_TESTING: {
961  if (StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker)) break;
962  return ComputeBuiltinFrameType(lookup_result.value());
963  }
964  case CodeKind::BASELINE:
965  // Baseline code can be deoptimized by DiscardBaselineCodeVisitor.
966  if (lookup_result.value()->marked_for_deoptimization())
967  return StackFrame::INTERPRETED;
968  return StackFrame::BASELINE;
969  case CodeKind::MAGLEV:
970  if (StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker)) {
971  // An INTERNAL frame can be set up with an associated Maglev code
972  // object when calling into runtime to handle tiering. In this case,
973  // all stack slots are tagged pointers and should be visited through
974  // the usual logic.
975  DCHECK_EQ(StackFrame::MarkerToType(marker), StackFrame::INTERNAL);
976  return StackFrame::INTERNAL;
977  }
978  return StackFrame::MAGLEV;
979  case CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS:
980  return StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS;
981 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
982  case CodeKind::JS_TO_WASM_FUNCTION:
983  if (lookup_result.value()->builtin_id() == Builtin::kJSToWasmWrapperAsm) {
984  return StackFrame::JS_TO_WASM;
985  }
986 #if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
987  if (lookup_result.value()->builtin_id() ==
988  Builtin::kGenericJSToWasmInterpreterWrapper) {
989  return StackFrame::JS_TO_WASM;
990  }
991 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
992  return StackFrame::TURBOFAN_STUB_WITH_CONTEXT;
993  case CodeKind::C_WASM_ENTRY:
994  return StackFrame::C_WASM_ENTRY;
995  case CodeKind::WASM_TO_JS_FUNCTION:
996  // Should have been found by the WasmCode lookup above.
997  UNREACHABLE();
998  case CodeKind::WASM_FUNCTION:
999  case CodeKind::WASM_TO_CAPI_FUNCTION:
1000  // These never appear as on-heap Code objects.
1001  UNREACHABLE();
1002 #else
1003  case CodeKind::C_WASM_ENTRY:
1004  case CodeKind::JS_TO_WASM_FUNCTION:
1005  case CodeKind::WASM_FUNCTION:
1006  case CodeKind::WASM_TO_CAPI_FUNCTION:
1007  case CodeKind::WASM_TO_JS_FUNCTION:
1008  UNREACHABLE();
1009 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1010  case CodeKind::BYTECODE_HANDLER:
1011  case CodeKind::REGEXP:
1012  case CodeKind::INTERPRETED_FUNCTION:
1013  // Fall back to the marker.
1014  break;
1015  }
1016 
1017  return SafeStackFrameType(StackFrame::MarkerToType(marker));
1018 }
1019 
1020 StackFrame::Type StackFrameIteratorForProfiler::ComputeStackFrameType(
1021  StackFrame::State* state) const {
1022 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1023  if (state->fp == kNullAddress) {
1024  DCHECK(!isolate_->wasm_stacks().empty()); // I.e., JSPI active
1025  return StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE;
1026  }
1027 #endif
1028 
1029  // We use unauthenticated_pc because it may come from
1030  // fast_c_call_caller_pc_address, for which authentication does not work.
1031  const Address pc = StackFrame::unauthenticated_pc(state->pc_address);
1032 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1033  if (IsWasmToJsWrapperCSA(pc)) {
1034  return StackFrame::WASM_TO_JS;
1035  }
1036 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1037 
1038  MSAN_MEMORY_IS_INITIALIZED(
1039  state->fp + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset,
1040  kSystemPointerSize);
1041  const intptr_t marker = Memory<intptr_t>(
1042  state->fp + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset);
1043  if (StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker)) {
1044  return SafeStackFrameType(StackFrame::MarkerToType(marker));
1045  }
1046 
1047  MSAN_MEMORY_IS_INITIALIZED(
1048  state->fp + StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset, kSystemPointerSize);
1049  Tagged<Object> maybe_function = Tagged<Object>(
1050  Memory<Address>(state->fp + StandardFrameConstants::kFunctionOffset));
1051  if (IsSmi(maybe_function)) {
1052  return StackFrame::NATIVE;
1053  }
1054 
1055  std::optional<bool> is_interpreter_frame =
1056  IsInterpreterFramePc(isolate(), pc, state);
1057 
1058  // We might not be able to lookup the frame type since we're inside a signal
1059  // handler and the required locks are taken.
1060  if (!is_interpreter_frame.has_value()) {
1061  return StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE;
1062  }
1063 
1064  if (is_interpreter_frame.value()) {
1065  return StackFrame::INTERPRETED;
1066  }
1067 
1068  return StackFrame::TURBOFAN_JS;
1069 }

1083  state->pc_address = ResolveReturnAddressLocation(

1097 StackFrame::Type EntryFrame::GetCallerState(State* state) const {
1098  const Address fast_c_call_caller_fp =
1099  Memory<Address>(fp() + EntryFrameConstants::kNextFastCallFrameFPOffset);
1100  if (fast_c_call_caller_fp != kNullAddress) {
1101  Address caller_pc_address =
1102  fp() + EntryFrameConstants::kNextFastCallFramePCOffset;
1103  Address caller_pc = Memory<Address>(caller_pc_address);
1104  return GetStateForFastCCallCallerFP(isolate(), fast_c_call_caller_fp,
1105  caller_pc, caller_pc_address, state);
1106  }
1107  Address next_exit_frame_fp =
1108  Memory<Address>(fp() + EntryFrameConstants::kNextExitFrameFPOffset);
1109  return ExitFrame::GetStateForFramePointer(next_exit_frame_fp, state);
1110 }

1133 void ExitFrame::ComputeCallerState(State* state) const {

1152 StackFrame::Type ExitFrame::GetStateForFramePointer(Address fp, State* state) {
1153  if (fp == 0) return NO_FRAME_TYPE;
1154  StackFrame::Type type = ComputeFrameType(fp);
1155 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1156  Address sp = type == WASM_EXIT ? WasmExitFrame::ComputeStackPointer(fp)
1157  : ExitFrame::ComputeStackPointer(fp);
1158 #else
1159  Address sp = ExitFrame::ComputeStackPointer(fp);
1160 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1161  FillState(fp, sp, state);
1162  DCHECK_NE(*state->pc_address, kNullAddress);
1163  return type;
1164 }
1165 
1166 StackFrame::Type ExitFrame::ComputeFrameType(Address fp) {
1167  // Distinguish between different exit frame types.
1168  // Default to EXIT in all hairy cases (e.g., when called from profiler).
1169  const int offset = ExitFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset;
1170  Tagged<Object> marker(Memory<Address>(fp + offset));
1171 
1172  if (!IsSmi(marker)) {
1173  return EXIT;
1174  }
1175 
1176  intptr_t marker_int = base::bit_cast<intptr_t>(marker);
1177 
1178  StackFrame::Type frame_type = static_cast<StackFrame::Type>(marker_int >> 1);
1179  switch (frame_type) {
1180  case BUILTIN_EXIT:
1181  case API_ACCESSOR_EXIT:
1182  case API_CALLBACK_EXIT:
1183 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1184  case WASM_EXIT:
1185  case STACK_SWITCH:
1186 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1187  return frame_type;
1188  default:
1189  return EXIT;
1190  }
1191 }

1194  MSAN_MEMORY_IS_INITIALIZED(fp + ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset,
1195  kSystemPointerSize);
1196  return Memory<Address>(fp + ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset);
1197 }

1199 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1200 Address WasmExitFrame::ComputeStackPointer(Address fp) {
1201  // For WASM_EXIT frames, {sp} is only needed for finding the PC slot,
1202  // everything else is handled via safepoint information.
1203  Address sp = fp + WasmExitFrameConstants::kWasmInstanceDataOffset;
1204  DCHECK_EQ(sp - 1 * kPCOnStackSize,
1205  fp + WasmExitFrameConstants::kCallingPCOffset);
1206  return sp;

1210 void ExitFrame::FillState(Address fp, Address sp, State* state) {
1211  state->sp = sp;
1212  state->fp = fp;
1213  state->pc_address = ResolveReturnAddressLocation(
1214  reinterpret_cast<Address*>(sp - 1 * kPCOnStackSize));
1215  state->callee_pc = kNullAddress;
1216  // The constant pool recorded in the exit frame is not associated
1217  // with the pc in this state (the return address into a C entry
1218  // stub). ComputeCallerState will retrieve the constant pool
1219  // together with the associated caller pc.
1220  state->constant_pool_address = nullptr;
1221 }

1500 void CommonFrame::ComputeCallerState(State* state) const {
1501  state->fp = caller_fp();
1502 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1503  if (state->fp == kNullAddress) {
1504  // An empty FP signals the first frame of a stack segment. The caller is
1505  // on a different stack, or is unbound (suspended stack).
1506  // DCHECK(isolate_->wasm_stacks() != nullptr); // I.e., JSPI active
1507  return;
1508  }
1509 #endif
1510  state->sp = caller_sp();
1511  state->pc_address = ResolveReturnAddressLocation(reinterpret_cast<Address*>(
1512  fp() + StandardFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset));
1513  state->callee_fp = fp();
1514  state->callee_pc = maybe_unauthenticated_pc();
1515  state->constant_pool_address = reinterpret_cast<Address*>(
1516  fp() + StandardFrameConstants::kConstantPoolOffset);
1517 }

1524 namespace {
1525 void VisitSpillSlot(Isolate* isolate, RootVisitor* v,
1526  FullObjectSlot spill_slot) {
1527 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
1528  PtrComprCageBase cage_base(isolate);
1529  bool was_compressed = false;
1530 
1531  // Spill slots may contain compressed values in which case the upper
1532  // 32-bits will contain zeros. In order to simplify handling of such
1533  // slots in GC we ensure that the slot always contains full value.
1534 
1535  // The spill slot may actually contain weak references so we load/store
1536  // values using spill_slot.location() in order to avoid dealing with
1537  // FullMaybeObjectSlots here.
1538  if (V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE_BOOL) {
1539  // When external code space is enabled the spill slot could contain both
1540  // InstructionStream and non-InstructionStream references, which have
1541  // different cage bases. So unconditional decompression of the value might
1542  // corrupt InstructionStream pointers. However, given that 1) the
1543  // InstructionStream pointers are never compressed by design (because
1544  // otherwise we wouldn't know which cage base to apply for
1545  // decompression, see respective DCHECKs in
1546  // RelocInfo::target_object()),
1547  // 2) there's no need to update the upper part of the full pointer
1548  // because if it was there then it'll stay the same,
1549  // we can avoid updating upper part of the spill slot if it already
1550  // contains full value.
1551  // TODO(v8:11880): Remove this special handling by enforcing builtins
1552  // to use CodeTs instead of InstructionStream objects.
1553  Address value = *spill_slot.location();
1554  if (!HAS_SMI_TAG(value) && value <= 0xffffffff) {
1555  // We don't need to update smi values or full pointers.
1556  was_compressed = true;
1557  *spill_slot.location() = V8HeapCompressionScheme::DecompressTagged(
1558  static_cast<Tagged_t>(value));
1559  if (DEBUG_BOOL) {
1560  // Ensure that the spill slot contains correct heap object.
1561  Tagged<HeapObject> raw =
1562  Cast<HeapObject>(Tagged<Object>(*spill_slot.location()));
1563  MapWord map_word = raw->map_word(cage_base, kRelaxedLoad);
1564  Tagged<HeapObject> forwarded = map_word.IsForwardingAddress()
1565  ? map_word.ToForwardingAddress(raw)
1566  : raw;
1567  bool is_self_forwarded =
1568  HeapLayout::IsSelfForwarded(forwarded, cage_base);
1569  if (is_self_forwarded) {
1570  // The object might be in a self-forwarding state if it's located
1571  // in new large object space. GC will fix this at a later stage.
1572  CHECK(
1573  MemoryChunk::FromHeapObject(forwarded)->InNewLargeObjectSpace() ||
1574  MemoryChunk::FromHeapObject(forwarded)->IsQuarantined());
1575  } else {
1576  Tagged<HeapObject> forwarded_map = forwarded->map(cage_base);
1577  // The map might be forwarded as well.
1578  MapWord fwd_map_map_word =
1579  forwarded_map->map_word(cage_base, kRelaxedLoad);
1580  if (fwd_map_map_word.IsForwardingAddress()) {
1581  forwarded_map = fwd_map_map_word.ToForwardingAddress(forwarded_map);
1582  }
1583  CHECK(IsMap(forwarded_map, cage_base));
1584  }
1585  }
1586  }
1587  } else {
1588  Address slot_contents = *spill_slot.location();
1589  Tagged_t compressed_value = static_cast<Tagged_t>(slot_contents);
1590  if (!HAS_SMI_TAG(compressed_value)) {
1591  was_compressed = slot_contents <= 0xFFFFFFFF;
1592  // We don't need to update smi values.
1593  *spill_slot.location() =
1594  V8HeapCompressionScheme::DecompressTagged(compressed_value);
1595  }
1596  }
1597 #endif
1598  v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, spill_slot);
1599 #if V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
1600  if (was_compressed) {
1601  // Restore compression. Generated code should be able to trust that
1602  // compressed spill slots remain compressed.
1603  *spill_slot.location() =
1604  V8HeapCompressionScheme::CompressObject(*spill_slot.location());
1605  }
1606 #endif
1607 }
1608 
1609 void VisitSpillSlots(Isolate* isolate, RootVisitor* v,
1610  FullObjectSlot first_slot_offset,
1611  base::Vector<const uint8_t> tagged_slots) {
1612  FullObjectSlot slot_offset = first_slot_offset;
1613  for (uint8_t bits : tagged_slots) {
1614  while (bits) {
1615  const int bit = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros(bits);
1616  bits &= ~(1 << bit);
1617  FullObjectSlot spill_slot = slot_offset + bit;
1618  VisitSpillSlot(isolate, v, spill_slot);
1619  }
1620  slot_offset += kBitsPerByte;
1621  }
1622 }

1658 // Class DrumBrakeWasmCode is an adapter class that exposes just the accessors
1659 // of the original WasmCode class that are used in WasmFrame::Iterate. For non
1660 // DrumBrake frames, the class calls the corresponding accessor in a contained
1661 // WasmCode object, while for DrumBrake frames it returns dummy values. This is
1662 // useful to minimize the merge issues in WasmFrame::Iterate.

1669  return std::make_unique<DrumBrakeWasmCode>(nullptr);
1670  }
1671  static std::unique_ptr<DrumBrakeWasmCode> Compiled(
1672  wasm::WasmCode* wasm_code) {
1673  return std::make_unique<DrumBrakeWasmCode>(wasm_code);
1674  }
1675 
1676  bool is_liftoff() const {
1677  return wasm_code_ ? wasm_code_->is_liftoff() : false;
1678  }
1679  bool frame_has_feedback_slot() const {
1680  return wasm_code_ ? wasm_code_->frame_has_feedback_slot() : false;
1681  }
1682  int stack_slots() const { return wasm_code_ ? wasm_code_->stack_slots() : 0; }
1683  wasm::WasmCode::Kind kind() const {
1684  return wasm_code_ ? wasm_code_->kind() : wasm::WasmCode::kInterpreterEntry;
1685  }
1686  uint16_t first_tagged_parameter_slot() const {
1687  return wasm_code_ ? wasm_code_->first_tagged_parameter_slot() : 0;
1688  }
1689  uint16_t num_tagged_parameter_slots() const {
1690  return wasm_code_ ? wasm_code_->num_tagged_parameter_slots() : 0;
1691  }
1692 
1693  private:
1694  const wasm::WasmCode* wasm_code_;
1695 };

1697 
1698 void WasmFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
1699  DCHECK(!iterator_->IsStackFrameIteratorForProfiler());
1700 
1701  // === WasmFrame ===
1702  // +-------------------------+-----------------------------------------
1703  // | out_param n | <-- parameters_base / sp
1704  // | ... |
1705  // | out_param 0 | (these can be tagged or untagged)
1706  // +-------------------------+-----------------------------------------
1707  // | spill_slot n | <-- parameters_limit ^
1708  // | ... | spill_slot_space
1709  // | spill_slot 0 | v
1710  // +-------------------------+-----------------------------------------
1711  // | WasmFeedback(*) | <-- frame_header_base ^
1712  // |- - - - - - - - - - - - -| |
1713  // | WasmTrustedInstanceData | |
1714  // |- - - - - - - - - - - - -| |
1715  // | Type Marker | |
1716  // |- - - - - - - - - - - - -| frame_header_size
1717  // | [Constant Pool] | |
1718  // |- - - - - - - - - - - - -| |
1719  // | saved frame ptr | <-- fp |
1720  // |- - - - - - - - - - - - -| |
1721  // | return addr | <-- tagged_parameter_limit v
1722  // +-------------------------+-----------------------------------------
1723  // | in_param n |
1724  // | ... |
1725  // | in_param 0 | <-- first_tagged_parameter_slot
1726  // +-------------------------+-----------------------------------------
1727  //
1728  // (*) Only if compiled by Liftoff and with --wasm-inlining.
1729 
1730 #if !V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1731  auto pair = wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCodeAndSafepoint(
1732  isolate(), maybe_unauthenticated_pc());
1733  wasm::WasmCode* wasm_code = pair.first;
1734  SafepointEntry safepoint_entry = pair.second;
1735 #else // !V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1736  std::unique_ptr<DrumBrakeWasmCode> interpreter_wasm_code;
1737  SafepointEntry safepoint_entry;
1738  bool is_wasm_interpreter_frame =
1739  v8_flags.wasm_jitless &&
1740  (type() == WASM_INTERPRETER_ENTRY || type() == C_WASM_ENTRY);
1741  if (is_wasm_interpreter_frame) {
1742  interpreter_wasm_code = DrumBrakeWasmCode::Interpreted();
1743  } else {
1744  auto pair =
1745  wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCodeAndSafepoint(isolate(), pc());
1746  wasm::WasmCode* wasm_code = pair.first;
1747  safepoint_entry = pair.second;
1748  DCHECK(wasm_code);
1749  interpreter_wasm_code = DrumBrakeWasmCode::Compiled(wasm_code);
1750  }
1751 
1752  // Reuse the same name "wasm_code" for this variable, to use the
1753  // DrumBrakeWasmCode adapter and minimize merge issues in the following code.
1754  DrumBrakeWasmCode* wasm_code = interpreter_wasm_code.get();
1755 #endif // !V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
1756 
1757 #ifdef DEBUG
1758  intptr_t marker =
1759  Memory<intptr_t>(fp() + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset);
1760  DCHECK(StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker));
1761  StackFrame::Type type = StackFrame::MarkerToType(marker);
1762  DCHECK(type == WASM_TO_JS || type == WASM || type == WASM_EXIT ||
1763  type == WASM_SEGMENT_START);
1764 #endif
1765 
1766  // Determine the fixed header and spill slot area size.
1767  // The last value in the frame header is the calling PC, which should
1768  // not be visited.
1769  static_assert(WasmExitFrameConstants::kFixedSlotCountFromFp ==
1770  WasmFrameConstants::kFixedSlotCountFromFp + 1,
1771  "WasmExitFrame has one slot more than WasmFrame");
1772 
1773  int frame_header_size = WasmFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp;
1774  if (wasm_code->is_liftoff() && wasm_code->frame_has_feedback_slot()) {
1775  // Frame has Wasm feedback slot.
1776  frame_header_size += kSystemPointerSize;
1777  }
1778  int spill_slot_space =
1779  wasm_code->stack_slots() * kSystemPointerSize -
1780  (frame_header_size + StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp);
1781  // Fixed frame slots.
1782  FullObjectSlot frame_header_base(&Memory<Address>(fp() - frame_header_size));
1783  FullObjectSlot frame_header_limit(
1784  &Memory<Address>(fp() - StandardFrameConstants::kCPSlotSize));
1785 
1786  // Visit parameters passed to the callee.
1787  // Frame layout without stack switching (stack grows upwards):
1788  //
1789  // | callee |
1790  // | frame |
1791  // |-------------| <- sp()
1792  // | out params |
1793  // |-------------| <- frame_header_base - spill_slot_space
1794  // | spill slots |
1795  // |-------------| <- frame_header_base
1796  // | frame header|
1797  // |-------------| <- fp()
1798  //
1799  // With stack-switching:
1800  //
1801  // Secondary stack: Central stack:
1802  //
1803  // | callee |
1804  // | frame |
1805  // |------------| <- sp()
1806  // | out params |
1807  // |-------------| |------------| <- maybe_stack_switch.target_sp
1808  // | spill slots |
1809  // |-------------| <- frame_header_base
1810  // | frame header|
1811  // |-------------| <- fp()
1812  //
1813  // The base (lowest address) of the outgoing stack parameters area is always
1814  // sp(), and the limit (highest address) is either {frame_header_base -
1815  // spill_slot_space} or {maybe_stack_switch.target_sp} depending on
1816  // stack-switching.
1817  wasm::StackMemory::StackSwitchInfo maybe_stack_switch;
1818  if (iterator_->wasm_stack() != nullptr) {
1819  maybe_stack_switch = iterator_->wasm_stack()->stack_switch_info();
1820  }
1821  FullObjectSlot parameters_limit(
1822  maybe_stack_switch.has_value() && maybe_stack_switch.source_fp == fp()
1823  ? maybe_stack_switch.target_sp
1824  : frame_header_base.address() - spill_slot_space);
1825  FullObjectSlot spill_space_end =
1826  FullObjectSlot(frame_header_base.address() - spill_slot_space);
1827 
1828  // Visit the rest of the parameters if they are tagged.
1829  bool has_tagged_outgoing_params =
1830  wasm_code->kind() != wasm::WasmCode::kWasmFunction &&
1831  wasm_code->kind() != wasm::WasmCode::kWasmToCapiWrapper;
1832  if (!InFastCCall() && has_tagged_outgoing_params) {
1833  FullObjectSlot parameters_base(&Memory<Address>(sp()));
1834  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, parameters_base,
1835  parameters_limit);
1836  }
1837 
1838  // Visit pointer spill slots and locals.
1839  if (safepoint_entry.is_initialized()) {
1840  DCHECK_GE((wasm_code->stack_slots() + kBitsPerByte) / kBitsPerByte,
1841  safepoint_entry.tagged_slots().size());
1842  VisitSpillSlots(isolate(), v, spill_space_end,
1843  safepoint_entry.tagged_slots());
1844  }
1845 
1846  // Visit tagged parameters that have been passed to the function of this
1847  // frame. Conceptionally these parameters belong to the parent frame. However,
1848  // the exact count is only known by this frame (in the presence of tail calls,
1849  // this information cannot be derived from the call site).
1850  if (wasm_code->num_tagged_parameter_slots() > 0) {
1851  FullObjectSlot tagged_parameter_base(&Memory<Address>(caller_sp()));
1852  tagged_parameter_base += wasm_code->first_tagged_parameter_slot();
1853  FullObjectSlot tagged_parameter_limit =
1854  tagged_parameter_base + wasm_code->num_tagged_parameter_slots();
1855 
1856  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, tagged_parameter_base,
1857  tagged_parameter_limit);
1858  }
1859 
1860  // Visit the instance object.
1861  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, frame_header_base,
1862  frame_header_limit);
1863 }
1864 
1865 void TypedFrame::IterateParamsOfGenericWasmToJSWrapper(RootVisitor* v) const {
1866  Address maybe_sig =
1867  Memory<Address>(fp() + WasmToJSWrapperConstants::kSignatureOffset);
1868  if (maybe_sig == 0 || maybe_sig == static_cast<Address>(-1)) {
1869  // The signature slot was reset after processing all incoming parameters.
1870  // We don't have to keep them alive anymore.
1871  return;
1872  }
1873 
1874  const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig =
1875  reinterpret_cast<wasm::CanonicalSig*>(maybe_sig);
1876  DCHECK(wasm::GetTypeCanonicalizer()->Contains(sig));
1877  wasm::LinkageLocationAllocator allocator(wasm::kGpParamRegisters,
1878  wasm::kFpParamRegisters, 0);
1879  // The first parameter is the instance data, which we don't have to scan. We
1880  // have to tell the LinkageLocationAllocator about it though.
1881  allocator.Next(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
1882 
1883  // Parameters are separated into two groups (first all untagged, then all
1884  // tagged parameters). Therefore we first have to iterate over the signature
1885  // first to process all untagged parameters, and afterwards we can scan the
1886  // tagged parameters.
1887  bool has_tagged_param = false;
1888  for (wasm::CanonicalValueType type : sig->parameters()) {
1889  MachineRepresentation param = type.machine_representation();
1890  // Skip tagged parameters (e.g. any-ref).
1891  if (IsAnyTagged(param)) {
1892  has_tagged_param = true;
1893  continue;
1894  }
1895  if (kSystemPointerSize == 8 || param != MachineRepresentation::kWord64) {
1896  allocator.Next(param);
1897  } else {
1898  allocator.Next(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
1899  allocator.Next(MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
1900  }
1901  }
1902 
1903  // End the untagged area, so tagged slots come after. This means, especially,
1904  // that tagged parameters should not fill holes in the untagged area.
1905  allocator.EndSlotArea();
1906 
1907  if (!has_tagged_param) return;
1908 
1909 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64
1910  constexpr size_t size_of_sig = 2;
1911 #else
1912  constexpr size_t size_of_sig = 1;
1913 #endif
1914 
1915  for (wasm::CanonicalValueType type : sig->parameters()) {
1916  MachineRepresentation param = type.machine_representation();
1917  // Skip untagged parameters.
1918  if (!IsAnyTagged(param)) continue;
1919  LinkageLocation l = allocator.Next(param);
1920  if (l.IsRegister()) {
1921  // Calculate the slot offset.
1922  int slot_offset = 0;
1923  // We have to do a reverse lookup in the kGPParamRegisters array. This
1924  // can be optimized if necessary.
1925  for (size_t i = 1; i < arraysize(wasm::kGpParamRegisters); ++i) {
1926  if (wasm::kGpParamRegisters[i].code() == l.AsRegister()) {
1927  // The first register (the instance) does not get spilled.
1928  slot_offset = static_cast<int>(i) - 1;
1929  break;
1930  }
1931  }
1932  // Caller FP + return address + signature.
1933  size_t param_start_offset = 2 + size_of_sig;
1934  FullObjectSlot param_start(fp() +
1935  param_start_offset * kSystemPointerSize);
1936  FullObjectSlot tagged_slot = param_start + slot_offset;
1937  VisitSpillSlot(isolate(), v, tagged_slot);
1938  } else {
1939  // Caller frame slots have negative indices and start at -1. Flip it
1940  // back to a positive offset (to be added to the frame's FP to find the
1941  // slot).
1942  int slot_offset = -l.GetLocation() - 1;
1943  // Caller FP + return address + signature + spilled registers (without the
1944  // instance register).
1945  size_t slots_per_float64 = kDoubleSize / kSystemPointerSize;
1946  size_t param_start_offset =
1947  arraysize(wasm::kGpParamRegisters) - 1 +
1948  (arraysize(wasm::kFpParamRegisters) * slots_per_float64) + 2 +
1949  size_of_sig;
1950 
1951  // The wasm-to-js wrapper pushes all but the first gp parameter register
1952  // on the stack, so if the number of gp parameter registers is even, this
1953  // means that the wrapper pushed an odd number. In that case, and when the
1954  // size of a double on the stack is two words, then there is an alignment
1955  // word between the pushed gp registers and the pushed fp registers, so
1956  // that the whole spill area is double-size aligned.
1957  if (arraysize(wasm::kGpParamRegisters) % 2 == (0) &&
1958  kSystemPointerSize != kDoubleSize) {
1959  param_start_offset++;
1960  }
1961  FullObjectSlot param_start(fp() +
1962  param_start_offset * kSystemPointerSize);
1963  FullObjectSlot tagged_slot = param_start + slot_offset;
1964  VisitSpillSlot(isolate(), v, tagged_slot);
1965  }
1966  }
1967 }
1968 
1969 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1970 
1971 void TypedFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
1972  DCHECK(!iterator_->IsStackFrameIteratorForProfiler());
1973 
1974  // === TypedFrame ===
1975  // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
1976  // | out_param n | <-- parameters_base / sp
1977  // | ... |
1978  // | out_param 0 |
1979  // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
1980  // | spill_slot n | <-- parameters_limit ^
1981  // | ... | spill_slot_count
1982  // | spill_slot 0 | v
1983  // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
1984  // | Type Marker | <-- frame_header_base ^
1985  // |- - - - - - - - -| |
1986  // | [Constant Pool] | |
1987  // |- - - - - - - - -| kFixedSlotCount
1988  // | saved frame ptr | <-- fp |
1989  // |- - - - - - - - -| |
1990  // | return addr | v
1991  // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
1992 
1993  // Find the code and compute the safepoint information.
1994  Address inner_pointer = pc();
1995  InnerPointerToCodeCache::InnerPointerToCodeCacheEntry* entry =
1996  isolate()->inner_pointer_to_code_cache()->GetCacheEntry(inner_pointer);
1997  CHECK(entry->code.has_value());
1998  Tagged<GcSafeCode> code = entry->code.value();
1999 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2000  bool is_generic_wasm_to_js =
2001  code->is_builtin() && code->builtin_id() == Builtin::kWasmToJsWrapperCSA;
2002  // Optimized wasm-to-js frames map to the WasmFrame type.
2003  DCHECK_NE(this->type(), WASM_TO_JS);
2004  if (is_generic_wasm_to_js) {
2005  IterateParamsOfGenericWasmToJSWrapper(v);
2006  }
2007 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2008  DCHECK(code->is_turbofanned());
2009  SafepointEntry safepoint_entry =
2010  GetSafepointEntryFromCodeCache(isolate(), inner_pointer, entry);
2011 
2012 #ifdef DEBUG
2013  intptr_t marker =
2014  Memory<intptr_t>(fp() + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset);
2015  DCHECK(StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker));
2016 #endif // DEBUG
2017 
2018  // Determine the fixed header and spill slot area size.
2019  int frame_header_size = TypedFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp;
2020  int spill_slots_size =
2021  code->stack_slots() * kSystemPointerSize -
2022  (frame_header_size + StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp);
2023 
2024  // Fixed frame slots.
2025  FullObjectSlot frame_header_base(&Memory<Address>(fp() - frame_header_size));
2026  FullObjectSlot frame_header_limit(
2027  &Memory<Address>(fp() - StandardFrameConstants::kCPSlotSize));
2028  // Parameters passed to the callee.
2029 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2030  // Frame layout without stack switching (stack grows upwards):
2031  //
2032  // | callee |
2033  // | frame |
2034  // |-------------| <- sp()
2035  // | out params |
2036  // |-------------| <- frame_header_base - spill_slot_space
2037  // | spill slots |
2038  // |-------------| <- frame_header_base
2039  // | frame header|
2040  // |-------------| <- fp()
2041  //
2042  // With stack-switching:
2043  //
2044  // Secondary stack: Central stack:
2045  //
2046  // | callee |
2047  // | frame |
2048  // |------------| <- sp()
2049  // | out params |
2050  // |-------------| |------------| <- maybe_stack_switch.target_sp
2051  // | spill slots |
2052  // |-------------| <- frame_header_base
2053  // | frame header|
2054  // |-------------| <- fp()
2055  //
2056  // The base (lowest address) of the outgoing stack parameters area is always
2057  // sp(), and the limit (highest address) is either {frame_header_base -
2058  // spill_slot_size} or {maybe_stack_switch.target_sp} depending on
2059  // stack-switching.
2060  wasm::StackMemory::StackSwitchInfo maybe_stack_switch;
2061  if (iterator_->wasm_stack() != nullptr) {
2062  maybe_stack_switch = iterator_->wasm_stack()->stack_switch_info();
2063  }
2064  FullObjectSlot parameters_limit(
2065  maybe_stack_switch.has_value() && maybe_stack_switch.source_fp == fp()
2066  ? maybe_stack_switch.target_sp
2067  : frame_header_base.address() - spill_slots_size);
2068 #else
2069  FullObjectSlot parameters_limit(frame_header_base.address() -
2070  spill_slots_size);
2071 #endif
2072  FullObjectSlot parameters_base(&Memory<Address>(sp()));
2073  FullObjectSlot spill_slots_end(frame_header_base.address() -
2074  spill_slots_size);
2075 
2076  // Visit the rest of the parameters.
2077  if (HasTaggedOutgoingParams(code)) {
2078  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, parameters_base,
2079  parameters_limit);
2080  }
2081 
2082  // Visit pointer spill slots and locals.
2083  DCHECK_GE((code->stack_slots() + kBitsPerByte) / kBitsPerByte,
2084  safepoint_entry.tagged_slots().size());
2085  VisitSpillSlots(isolate(), v, spill_slots_end,
2086  safepoint_entry.tagged_slots());
2087 
2088  // Visit fixed header region.
2089  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, frame_header_base,
2090  frame_header_limit);
2091 
2092  // Visit the return address in the callee and incoming arguments.
2093  IteratePc(v, constant_pool_address(), code);
2094 }
2095 
2096 void MaglevFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
2097  DCHECK(!iterator_->IsStackFrameIteratorForProfiler());
2098 
2099  // === MaglevFrame ===
2100  // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2101  // | out_param n | <-- parameters_base / sp
2102  // | ... |
2103  // | out_param 0 |
2104  // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2105  // | pushed_double n | <-- parameters_limit ^
2106  // | ... | |
2107  // | pushed_double 0 | |
2108  // +- - - - - - - - -+ num_extra_spill_slots
2109  // | pushed_reg n | |
2110  // | ... | |
2111  // | pushed_reg 0 | <-- pushed_register_base v
2112  // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2113  // | untagged_slot n | ^
2114  // | ... | |
2115  // | untagged_slot 0 | |
2116  // +- - - - - - - - -+ spill_slot_count
2117  // | tagged_slot n | |
2118  // | ... | |
2119  // | tagged_slot 0 | v
2120  // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2121  // | argc | <-- frame_header_base ^
2122  // |- - - - - - - - -| |
2123  // | JSFunction | |
2124  // |- - - - - - - - -| |
2125  // | Context | |
2126  // |- - - - - - - - -| kFixedSlotCount
2127  // | [Constant Pool] | |
2128  // |- - - - - - - - -| |
2129  // | saved frame ptr | <-- fp |
2130  // |- - - - - - - - -| |
2131  // | return addr | v
2132  // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2133 
2134  // Find the code and compute the safepoint information.
2135  Address inner_pointer = pc();
2136  InnerPointerToCodeCache::InnerPointerToCodeCacheEntry* entry =
2137  isolate()->inner_pointer_to_code_cache()->GetCacheEntry(inner_pointer);
2138  CHECK(entry->code.has_value());
2139  Tagged<GcSafeCode> code = entry->code.value();
2140  DCHECK(code->is_maglevved());
2141  MaglevSafepointEntry maglev_safepoint_entry =
2142  GetMaglevSafepointEntryFromCodeCache(isolate(), inner_pointer, entry);
2143 
2144 #ifdef DEBUG
2145  // Assert that it is a JS frame and it has a context.
2146  intptr_t marker =
2147  Memory<intptr_t>(fp() + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset);
2148  DCHECK(!StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker));
2149 #endif // DEBUG
2150 
2151  // Fixed frame slots.
2152  FullObjectSlot frame_header_base(
2153  &Memory<Address>(fp() - StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp));
2154  FullObjectSlot frame_header_limit(
2155  &Memory<Address>(fp() - StandardFrameConstants::kCPSlotSize));
2156 
2157  // Determine spill slot area count.
2158  uint32_t tagged_slot_count = maglev_safepoint_entry.num_tagged_slots();
2159  uint32_t spill_slot_count =
2160  code->stack_slots() - StandardFrameConstants::kFixedSlotCount;
2161 
2162  // Visit the outgoing parameters if they are tagged.
2163  DCHECK(code->has_tagged_outgoing_params());
2164  FullObjectSlot parameters_base(&Memory<Address>(sp()));
2165  FullObjectSlot parameters_limit =
2166  frame_header_base - spill_slot_count -
2167  maglev_safepoint_entry.num_extra_spill_slots();
2168  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, parameters_base,
2169  parameters_limit);
2170 
2171  // Maglev can also spill registers, tagged and untagged, just before making
2172  // a call. These are distinct from normal spill slots and live between the
2173  // normal spill slots and the pushed parameters. Some of these are tagged,
2174  // as indicated by the tagged register indexes, and should be visited too.
2175  if (maglev_safepoint_entry.num_extra_spill_slots() > 0) {
2176  FullObjectSlot pushed_register_base =
2177  frame_header_base - spill_slot_count - 1;
2178  uint32_t tagged_register_indexes =
2179  maglev_safepoint_entry.tagged_register_indexes();
2180  while (tagged_register_indexes != 0) {
2181  int index = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros(tagged_register_indexes);
2182  tagged_register_indexes &= ~(1 << index);
2183  FullObjectSlot spill_slot = pushed_register_base - index;
2184  VisitSpillSlot(isolate(), v, spill_slot);
2185  }
2186  }
2187 
2188  // Visit tagged spill slots.
2189  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < tagged_slot_count; ++i) {
2190  FullObjectSlot spill_slot = frame_header_base - 1 - i;
2191  VisitSpillSlot(isolate(), v, spill_slot);
2192  }
2193 
2194  // Visit fixed header region (the context and JSFunction), skipping the
2195  // argument count since it is stored untagged.
2196  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, frame_header_base + 1,
2197  frame_header_limit);
2198 
2199  // Visit the return address in the callee and incoming arguments.
2200  IteratePc(v, constant_pool_address(), code);
2201 }

2203 DirectHandle<JSFunction> MaglevFrame::GetInnermostFunction() const {
2204  return Summarize().frames.back().AsJavaScript().function();
2205 }

2207 BytecodeOffset MaglevFrame::GetBytecodeOffsetForOSR() const {
2208  int deopt_index = SafepointEntry::kNoDeoptIndex;
2209  Tagged<Code> code = LookupCode();
2210  const Tagged<DeoptimizationData> data =
2211  GetDeoptimizationData(code, &deopt_index);
2212  if (deopt_index == SafepointEntry::kNoDeoptIndex) {
2213  CHECK(data.is_null());
2214  FATAL(
2215  "Missing deoptimization information for OptimizedJSFrame::Summarize.");
2216  }
2217 
2218  DeoptimizationFrameTranslation::Iterator it(
2219  data->FrameTranslation(), data->TranslationIndex(deopt_index).value());
2220  // Search the innermost interpreter frame and get its bailout id. The
2221  // translation stores frames bottom up.
2222  int js_frames = it.EnterBeginOpcode().js_frame_count;
2223  DCHECK_GT(js_frames, 0);
2224  BytecodeOffset offset = BytecodeOffset::None();
2225  while (js_frames > 0) {
2226  TranslationOpcode frame = it.SeekNextJSFrame();
2227  --js_frames;
2228  if (IsTranslationInterpreterFrameOpcode(frame)) {
2229  offset = BytecodeOffset(it.NextOperand());
2230  it.SkipOperands(TranslationOpcodeOperandCount(frame) - 1);
2231  } else {
2232  it.SkipOperands(TranslationOpcodeOperandCount(frame));
2233  }
2234  }
2235 
2236  return offset;
2237 }

2239 bool CommonFrame::HasTaggedOutgoingParams(
2240  Tagged<GcSafeCode> code_lookup) const {
2241 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2242  // With inlined JS-to-Wasm calls, we can be in an OptimizedJSFrame and
2243  // directly call a Wasm function from JavaScript. In this case the Wasm frame
2244  // is responsible for visiting incoming potentially tagged parameters.
2245  // (This is required for tail-call support: If the direct callee tail-called
2246  // another function which then caused a GC, the caller would not be able to
2247  // determine where there might be tagged parameters.)
2248  wasm::WasmCode* wasm_callee =
2249  wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCode(isolate(), callee_pc());
2250  if (wasm_callee) return false;
2251 
2252  if (IsWasmToJsWrapperCSA(callee_pc())) {
2253  return false;
2254  }
2255  return code_lookup->has_tagged_outgoing_params();
2256 #else
2257  return code_lookup->has_tagged_outgoing_params();
2258 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2259 }

2261 Tagged<HeapObject> TurbofanStubWithContextFrame::unchecked_code() const {
2262  std::optional<Tagged<GcSafeCode>> code_lookup =
2263  isolate()->heap()->GcSafeTryFindCodeForInnerPointer(pc());
2264  if (!code_lookup.has_value()) return {};
2265  return code_lookup.value();

2268 void CommonFrame::IterateTurbofanJSOptimizedFrame(RootVisitor* v) const {
2269  DCHECK(!iterator_->IsStackFrameIteratorForProfiler());
2270 
2271  // === TurbofanJSFrame ===
2272  // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2273  // | out_param n | <-- parameters_base / sp
2274  // | ... |
2275  // | out_param 0 |
2276  // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2277  // | spill_slot n | <-- parameters_limit ^
2278  // | ... | spill_slot_count
2279  // | spill_slot 0 | v
2280  // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2281  // | argc | <-- frame_header_base ^
2282  // |- - - - - - - - -| |
2283  // | JSFunction | |
2284  // |- - - - - - - - -| |
2285  // | Context | |
2286  // |- - - - - - - - -| kFixedSlotCount
2287  // | [Constant Pool] | |
2288  // |- - - - - - - - -| |
2289  // | saved frame ptr | <-- fp |
2290  // |- - - - - - - - -| |
2291  // | return addr | v
2292  // +-----------------+-----------------------------------------
2293 
2294  // Find the code and compute the safepoint information.
2295  const Address inner_pointer = maybe_unauthenticated_pc();
2296  InnerPointerToCodeCache::InnerPointerToCodeCacheEntry* entry =
2297  isolate()->inner_pointer_to_code_cache()->GetCacheEntry(inner_pointer);
2298  CHECK(entry->code.has_value());
2299  Tagged<GcSafeCode> code = entry->code.value();
2300  DCHECK(code->is_turbofanned());
2301  SafepointEntry safepoint_entry =
2302  GetSafepointEntryFromCodeCache(isolate(), inner_pointer, entry);
2303 
2304 #ifdef DEBUG
2305  // Assert that it is a JS frame and it has a context.
2306  intptr_t marker =
2307  Memory<intptr_t>(fp() + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset);
2308  DCHECK(!StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker));
2309 #endif // DEBUG
2310 
2311  // Determine the fixed header and spill slot area size.
2312  int frame_header_size = StandardFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp;
2313  int spill_slot_count =
2314  code->stack_slots() - StandardFrameConstants::kFixedSlotCount;
2315 
2316  // Fixed frame slots.
2317  FullObjectSlot frame_header_base(&Memory<Address>(fp() - frame_header_size));
2318  FullObjectSlot frame_header_limit(
2319  &Memory<Address>(fp() - StandardFrameConstants::kCPSlotSize));
2320 
2321  FullObjectSlot parameters_limit = frame_header_base - spill_slot_count;
2322 
2323  if (!InFastCCall()) {
2324  // Parameters passed to the callee.
2325  FullObjectSlot parameters_base(&Memory<Address>(sp()));
2326 
2327  // Visit the outgoing parameters if they are tagged.
2328  if (HasTaggedOutgoingParams(code)) {
2329  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, parameters_base,
2330  parameters_limit);
2331  }
2332  } else {
2333  // There are no outgoing parameters to visit for fast C calls.
2334  }
2335 
2336  // Spill slots are in the region ]frame_header_base, parameters_limit];
2337  // Visit pointer spill slots and locals.
2338  DCHECK_GE((code->stack_slots() + kBitsPerByte) / kBitsPerByte,
2339  safepoint_entry.tagged_slots().size());
2340  VisitSpillSlots(isolate(), v, parameters_limit,
2341  safepoint_entry.tagged_slots());
2342 
2343  // Visit fixed header region (the context and JSFunction), skipping the
2344  // argument count since it is stored untagged.
2345  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, frame_header_base + 1,
2346  frame_header_limit);
2347 
2348  // Visit the return address in the callee and incoming arguments.
2349  IteratePc(v, constant_pool_address(), code);
2350 }

2377 FrameSummaries StubFrame::Summarize() const {
2378  FrameSummaries summaries;
2379 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2380  Tagged<Code> code = LookupCode();
2381  if (code->kind() != CodeKind::BUILTIN) return summaries;
2382  // We skip most stub frames from stack traces, but a few builtins
2383  // specifically exist to pretend to be another builtin throwing an
2384  // exception.
2385  switch (code->builtin_id()) {
2386  case Builtin::kThrowDataViewTypeError:
2387  case Builtin::kThrowDataViewDetachedError:
2388  case Builtin::kThrowDataViewOutOfBounds:
2389  case Builtin::kThrowIndexOfCalledOnNull:
2390  case Builtin::kThrowToLowerCaseCalledOnNull:
2391  case Builtin::kWasmIntToString: {
2392  // When adding builtins here, also implement naming support for them.
2393  DCHECK_NE(nullptr,
2394  Builtins::NameForStackTrace(isolate(), code->builtin_id()));
2395  FrameSummary::BuiltinFrameSummary summary(isolate(), code->builtin_id());
2396  summaries.frames.push_back(summary);
2397  break;
2398  }
2399  default:
2400  break;
2401  }
2402 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2403  return summaries;
2404 }

2449 std::tuple<Tagged<AbstractCode>, int> JavaScriptFrame::GetActiveCodeAndOffset()
2450  const {
2451  int code_offset = 0;
2452  Tagged<AbstractCode> abstract_code;
2453  if (is_interpreted()) {
2454  const InterpretedFrame* iframe = InterpretedFrame::cast(this);
2455  code_offset = iframe->GetBytecodeOffset();
2456  abstract_code = Cast<AbstractCode>(iframe->GetBytecodeArray());
2457  } else if (is_baseline()) {
2458  // TODO(pthier): AbstractCode should fully support Baseline code.
2459  const BaselineFrame* baseline_frame = BaselineFrame::cast(this);
2460  code_offset = baseline_frame->GetBytecodeOffset();
2461  abstract_code = Cast<AbstractCode>(baseline_frame->GetBytecodeArray());
2462  } else {
2463  Tagged<Code> code;
2464  int pc_offset = -1;
2465  std::tie(code, pc_offset) = LookupCodeAndOffset();
2466  abstract_code = Cast<AbstractCode>(code);
2467  }
2468  return {abstract_code, code_offset};
2469 }

2528 void JavaScriptFrame::PrintFunctionAndOffset(Isolate* isolate,
2529  Tagged<JSFunction> function,
2530  Tagged<AbstractCode> code,
2531  int code_offset, FILE* file,
2532  bool print_line_number) {
2533  PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase(function);
2534  PrintF(file, "%s", CodeKindToMarker(code->kind(cage_base), false));
2535  function->PrintName(file);
2536  PrintF(file, "+%d", code_offset);
2537  if (print_line_number) {
2538  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = function->shared();
2539  int source_pos = code->SourcePosition(isolate, code_offset);
2540  Tagged<Object> maybe_script = shared->script();
2541  if (IsScript(maybe_script)) {
2542  Tagged<Script> script = Cast<Script>(maybe_script);
2543  int line = script->GetLineNumber(source_pos) + 1;
2544  Tagged<Object> script_name_raw = script->name();
2545  if (IsString(script_name_raw)) {
2546  Tagged<String> script_name = Cast<String>(script->name());
2547  std::unique_ptr<char[]> c_script_name = script_name->ToCString();
2548  PrintF(file, " at %s:%d", c_script_name.get(), line);
2549  } else {
2550  PrintF(file, " at <unknown>:%d", line);
2551  }
2552  } else {
2553  PrintF(file, " at <unknown>:<unknown>");
2554  }
2555  }
2556 }
2557 
2558 void JavaScriptFrame::PrintTop(Isolate* isolate, FILE* file, bool print_args,
2559  bool print_line_number) {
2560  // constructor calls
2561  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2562  JavaScriptStackFrameIterator it(isolate);
2563  while (!it.done()) {
2564  if (it.frame()->is_javascript()) {
2565  JavaScriptFrame* frame = it.frame();
2566  if (frame->IsConstructor()) PrintF(file, "new ");
2567  Tagged<JSFunction> function = frame->function();
2568  int code_offset = 0;
2569  Tagged<AbstractCode> code;
2570  std::tie(code, code_offset) = frame->GetActiveCodeAndOffset();
2571  PrintFunctionAndOffset(isolate, function, code, code_offset, file,
2572  print_line_number);
2573  if (print_args) {
2574  // function arguments
2575  // (we are intentionally only printing the actually
2576  // supplied parameters, not all parameters required)
2577  PrintF(file, "(this=");
2578  ShortPrint(frame->receiver(), file);
2579  const int length = frame->ComputeParametersCount();
2580  for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
2581  PrintF(file, ", ");
2582  ShortPrint(frame->GetParameter(i), file);
2583  }
2584  PrintF(file, ")");
2585  }
2586  break;
2587  }
2588  it.Advance();
2589  }
2590 }

2592 // static
2593 void JavaScriptFrame::CollectFunctionAndOffsetForICStats(
2594  Isolate* isolate, Tagged<JSFunction> function, Tagged<AbstractCode> code,
2595  int code_offset) {
2596  auto ic_stats = ICStats::instance();
2597  ICInfo& ic_info = ic_stats->Current();
2598  PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase(function);
2599  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = function->shared(cage_base);
2600 
2601  ic_info.function_name = ic_stats->GetOrCacheFunctionName(isolate, function);
2602  ic_info.script_offset = code_offset;
2603 
2604  int source_pos = code->SourcePosition(isolate, code_offset);
2605  Tagged<Object> maybe_script = shared->script(cage_base, kAcquireLoad);
2606  if (IsScript(maybe_script, cage_base)) {
2607  Tagged<Script> script = Cast<Script>(maybe_script);
2608  Script::PositionInfo info;
2609  script->GetPositionInfo(source_pos, &info);
2610  ic_info.line_num = info.line + 1;
2611  ic_info.column_num = info.column + 1;
2612  ic_info.script_name = ic_stats->GetOrCacheScriptName(script);
2613  }
2614 }

2754 DirectHandle<StackFrameInfo>
2755 FrameSummary::JavaScriptFrameSummary::CreateStackFrameInfo() const {
2756  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(function_->shared(), isolate());
2757  DirectHandle<Script> script(Cast<Script>(shared->script()), isolate());
2758  DirectHandle<String> function_name =
2759  JSFunction::GetDebugName(isolate(), function_);
2760  if (function_name->length() == 0 &&
2761  script->compilation_type() == Script::CompilationType::kEval) {
2762  function_name = isolate()->factory()->eval_string();
2763  }
2764  int bytecode_offset = code_offset();
2765  if (bytecode_offset == kFunctionEntryBytecodeOffset) {
2766  // For the special function entry bytecode offset (-1), which signals
2767  // that the stack trace was captured while the function entry was
2768  // executing (i.e. during the interrupt check), we cannot store this
2769  // sentinel in the bit field, so we just eagerly lookup the source
2770  // position within the script.
2771  SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(isolate(), shared);
2772  int source_position =
2773  abstract_code()->SourcePosition(isolate(), bytecode_offset);
2774  return isolate()->factory()->NewStackFrameInfo(
2775  script, source_position, function_name, is_constructor());
2776  }
2777  return isolate()->factory()->NewStackFrameInfo(
2778  shared, bytecode_offset, function_name, is_constructor());
2779 }
