3029 FrameSummaries OptimizedJSFrame::Summarize() const {
3030  DCHECK(is_optimized());
3031  FrameSummaries summaries;
3032 
3033  // Delegate to JS frame in absence of deoptimization info.
3034  // TODO(turbofan): Revisit once we support deoptimization across the board.
3035  DirectHandle<Code> code(LookupCode(), isolate());
3036  if (code->kind() == CodeKind::BUILTIN ||
3037  code->kind() == CodeKind::FOR_TESTING) {
3038  return JavaScriptFrame::Summarize();
3039  }
3040 
3041  int deopt_index = SafepointEntry::kNoDeoptIndex;
3042  Tagged<DeoptimizationData> const data =
3043  GetDeoptimizationData(*code, &deopt_index);
3044  if (deopt_index == SafepointEntry::kNoDeoptIndex) {
3045  // Hack: For maglevved function entry, we don't emit lazy deopt information,
3046  // so create an extra special summary here.
3047  //
3048  // TODO(leszeks): Remove this hack, by having a maglev-specific frame
3049  // summary which is a bit more aware of maglev behaviour and can e.g. handle
3050  // more compact safepointed frame information for both function entry and
3051  // loop stack checks.
3052  if (code->is_maglevved()) {
3053  DirectHandle<AbstractCode> abstract_code(
3054  Cast<AbstractCode>(function()->shared()->GetBytecodeArray(isolate())),
3055  isolate());
3056  DirectHandle<FixedArray> params = GetParameters();
3057  FrameSummary::JavaScriptFrameSummary summary(
3058  isolate(), receiver(), function(), *abstract_code,
3059  kFunctionEntryBytecodeOffset, IsConstructor(), *params);
3060  summaries.frames.push_back(summary);
3061  return summaries;
3062  }
3063 
3064  CHECK(data.is_null());
3065  FATAL(
3066  "Missing deoptimization information for OptimizedJSFrame::Summarize.");
3067  }
3068 
3069  // Prepare iteration over translation. We must not materialize values here
3070  // because we do not deoptimize the function.
3071  TranslatedState translated(this);
3072  translated.Prepare(fp());
3073 
3074  // We create the summary in reverse order because the frames
3075  // in the deoptimization translation are ordered bottom-to-top.
3076  bool is_constructor = IsConstructor();
3077  for (auto it = translated.begin(); it != translated.end(); it++) {
3078  if (it->kind() == TranslatedFrame::kUnoptimizedFunction ||
3079  it->kind() == TranslatedFrame::kJavaScriptBuiltinContinuation ||
3080  it->kind() ==
3081  TranslatedFrame::kJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationWithCatch) {
3082  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info = it->shared_info();
3083 
3084  // The translation commands are ordered and the function is always
3085  // at the first position, and the receiver is next.
3086  TranslatedFrame::iterator translated_values = it->begin();
3087 
3088  // Get the correct function in the optimized frame.
3089  CHECK(!translated_values->IsMaterializedObject());
3090  DirectHandle<JSFunction> function =
3091  Cast<JSFunction>(translated_values->GetValue());
3092  translated_values++;
3093 
3094  // Get the correct receiver in the optimized frame.
3095  CHECK(!translated_values->IsMaterializedObject());
3096  DirectHandle<Object> receiver = translated_values->GetValue();
3097  translated_values++;
3098 
3099  // Determine the underlying code object and the position within it from
3100  // the translation corresponding to the frame type in question.
3101  DirectHandle<AbstractCode> abstract_code;
3102  unsigned code_offset;
3103  if (it->kind() == TranslatedFrame::kJavaScriptBuiltinContinuation ||
3104  it->kind() ==
3105  TranslatedFrame::kJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationWithCatch) {
3106  code_offset = 0;
3107  abstract_code = Cast<AbstractCode>(isolate()->builtins()->code_handle(
3108  Builtins::GetBuiltinFromBytecodeOffset(it->bytecode_offset())));
3109  } else {
3110  DCHECK_EQ(it->kind(), TranslatedFrame::kUnoptimizedFunction);
3111  code_offset = it->bytecode_offset().ToInt();
3112  abstract_code =
3113  direct_handle(shared_info->abstract_code(isolate()), isolate());
3114  }
3115 
3116  // Append full summary of the encountered JS frame.
3117  DirectHandle<FixedArray> params = GetParameters();
3118  FrameSummary::JavaScriptFrameSummary summary(
3119  isolate(), *receiver, *function, *abstract_code, code_offset,
3120  is_constructor, *params);
3121  summaries.frames.push_back(summary);
3122  is_constructor = false;
3123  } else if (it->kind() == TranslatedFrame::kConstructCreateStub ||
3124  it->kind() == TranslatedFrame::kConstructInvokeStub) {
3125  // The next encountered JS frame will be marked as a constructor call.
3126  DCHECK(!is_constructor);
3127  is_constructor = true;
3128 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3129  } else if (it->kind() == TranslatedFrame::kWasmInlinedIntoJS) {
3130  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info = it->shared_info();
3131  DCHECK_NE(isolate()->heap()->gc_state(), Heap::MARK_COMPACT);
3132 
3133  Tagged<WasmExportedFunctionData> function_data =
3134  shared_info->wasm_exported_function_data();
3135  Handle<WasmTrustedInstanceData> instance{function_data->instance_data(),
3136  isolate()};
3137  int func_index = function_data->function_index();
3138  FrameSummary::WasmInlinedFrameSummary summary(
3139  isolate(), instance, func_index, it->bytecode_offset().ToInt());
3140  summaries.frames.push_back(summary);
3141 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3142  }
3143  }
3144  if (is_constructor) {
3145  // If {is_constructor} is true, then we haven't inlined the constructor in
3146  // the optimized frames and the previous visited frame (top of the inlined
3147  // frames) is a construct call.
3148  summaries.top_frame_is_construct_call = true;
3149  }
3150  return summaries;
3151 }
3152 
3153 int OptimizedJSFrame::LookupExceptionHandlerInTable(
3154  int* data, HandlerTable::CatchPrediction* prediction) {
3155  // We cannot perform exception prediction on optimized code. Instead, we need
3156  // to use FrameSummary to find the corresponding code offset in unoptimized
3157  // code to perform prediction there.
3158  DCHECK_NULL(prediction);
3159  Tagged<Code> code;
3160  int pc_offset = -1;
3161  std::tie(code, pc_offset) = LookupCodeAndOffset();
3162 
3163  HandlerTable table(code);
3164  if (table.NumberOfReturnEntries() == 0) return -1;
3165 
3166  DCHECK_NULL(data); // Data is not used and will not return a value.
3167 
3168  // When the return pc has been replaced by a trampoline there won't be
3169  // a handler for this trampoline. Thus we need to use the return pc that
3170  // _used to be_ on the stack to get the right ExceptionHandler.
3171  if (CodeKindCanDeoptimize(code->kind())) {
3172  if (!code->marked_for_deoptimization()) {
3173  // Lazy deoptimize the function in case the handler table entry flags that
3174  // it wants to be lazily deoptimized on throw. This allows the optimizing
3175  // compiler to omit catch blocks that were never reached in practice.
3176  int optimized_exception_handler = table.LookupReturn(pc_offset);
3177  if (optimized_exception_handler != HandlerTable::kLazyDeopt) {
3178  return optimized_exception_handler;
3179  }
3180  Deoptimizer::DeoptimizeFunction(
3181  function(), LazyDeoptimizeReason::kExceptionCaught, code);
3182  }
3183  DCHECK(code->marked_for_deoptimization());
3184  pc_offset = FindReturnPCForTrampoline(code, pc_offset);
3185  }
3186  return table.LookupReturn(pc_offset);
3187 }
3188 
3189 int MaglevFrame::FindReturnPCForTrampoline(Tagged<Code> code,
3190  int trampoline_pc) const {
3191  DCHECK_EQ(code->kind(), CodeKind::MAGLEV);
3192  DCHECK(code->marked_for_deoptimization());
3193  MaglevSafepointTable safepoints(isolate(), pc(), code);
3194  return safepoints.find_return_pc(trampoline_pc);
3195 }
3196 
3197 int TurbofanJSFrame::FindReturnPCForTrampoline(Tagged<Code> code,
3198  int trampoline_pc) const {
3199  DCHECK_EQ(code->kind(), CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS);
3200  DCHECK(code->marked_for_deoptimization());
3201  SafepointTable safepoints(isolate(), pc(), code);
3202  return safepoints.find_return_pc(trampoline_pc);
3203 }
3204 
3205 Tagged<DeoptimizationData> OptimizedJSFrame::GetDeoptimizationData(
3206  Tagged<Code> code, int* deopt_index) const {
3207  DCHECK(is_optimized());
3208 
3209  Address pc = maybe_unauthenticated_pc();
3210 
3211  DCHECK(code->contains(isolate(), pc));
3212  DCHECK(CodeKindCanDeoptimize(code->kind()));
3213 
3214  if (code->is_maglevved()) {
3215  MaglevSafepointEntry safepoint_entry =
3216  code->GetMaglevSafepointEntry(isolate(), pc);
3217  if (safepoint_entry.has_deoptimization_index()) {
3218  *deopt_index = safepoint_entry.deoptimization_index();
3219  return Cast<DeoptimizationData>(code->deoptimization_data());
3220  }
3221  } else {
3222  SafepointEntry safepoint_entry = code->GetSafepointEntry(isolate(), pc);
3223  if (safepoint_entry.has_deoptimization_index()) {
3224  *deopt_index = safepoint_entry.deoptimization_index();
3225  return Cast<DeoptimizationData>(code->deoptimization_data());
3226  }
3227  }
3228  *deopt_index = SafepointEntry::kNoDeoptIndex;
3229  return {};
3230 }
3231 
3232 void OptimizedJSFrame::GetFunctions(
3233  std::vector<Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo>>* functions) const {
3234  DCHECK(functions->empty());
3235  DCHECK(is_optimized());
3236 
3237  // Delegate to JS frame in absence of turbofan deoptimization.
3238  // TODO(turbofan): Revisit once we support deoptimization across the board.
3239  Tagged<Code> code = LookupCode();
3240  if (code->kind() == CodeKind::BUILTIN) {
3241  return JavaScriptFrame::GetFunctions(functions);
3242  }
3243 
3244  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3245  int deopt_index = SafepointEntry::kNoDeoptIndex;
3246  Tagged<DeoptimizationData> const data =
3247  GetDeoptimizationData(code, &deopt_index);
3248  DCHECK(!data.is_null());
3249  DCHECK_NE(SafepointEntry::kNoDeoptIndex, deopt_index);
3250  Tagged<DeoptimizationLiteralArray> const literal_array = data->LiteralArray();
3251 
3252  DeoptimizationFrameTranslation::Iterator it(
3253  data->FrameTranslation(), data->TranslationIndex(deopt_index).value());
3254  int jsframe_count = it.EnterBeginOpcode().js_frame_count;
3255 
3256  // We insert the frames in reverse order because the frames
3257  // in the deoptimization translation are ordered bottom-to-top.
3258  while (jsframe_count != 0) {
3259  TranslationOpcode opcode = it.SeekNextJSFrame();
3260  it.NextOperand(); // Skip bailout id.
3261  jsframe_count--;
3262 
3263  // The second operand of the frame points to the function.
3264  Tagged<Object> shared = literal_array->get(it.NextOperand());
3265  functions->push_back(Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(shared));
3266 
3267  // Skip over remaining operands to advance to the next opcode.
3268  it.SkipOperands(TranslationOpcodeOperandCount(opcode) - 2);
3269  }
3270 }

3283 int UnoptimizedJSFrame::LookupExceptionHandlerInTable(
3284  int* context_register, HandlerTable::CatchPrediction* prediction) {
3285  HandlerTable table(GetBytecodeArray());
3286  int handler_index = table.LookupHandlerIndexForRange(GetBytecodeOffset());
3287  if (handler_index != HandlerTable::kNoHandlerFound) {
3288  if (context_register) *context_register = table.GetRangeData(handler_index);
3289  if (prediction) *prediction = table.GetRangePrediction(handler_index);
3290  table.MarkHandlerUsed(handler_index);
3291  return table.GetRangeHandler(handler_index);
3292  }
3293  return handler_index;
3294 }

3377 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY

3379  int index) const {
3380  PrintIndex(accumulator, mode, index);
3381 
3382 #if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
3383  if (v8_flags.wasm_jitless) {
3384  DCHECK(is_wasm_to_js());

3386  if (mode != OVERVIEW) accumulator->Add("\n");
3387  return;
3388  }
3389 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
3390 
3391  if (function_index() == wasm::kAnonymousFuncIndex) {
3392  accumulator->Add("Anonymous wasm wrapper [pc: %p]\n",
3393  reinterpret_cast<void*>(pc()));
3394  return;
3395  }

3397  accumulator->Add(is_wasm_to_js() ? "Wasm-to-JS [" : "Wasm [");
3398  accumulator->PrintName(script()->name());
3399  Address instruction_start = wasm_code()->instruction_start();
3400  base::Vector<const uint8_t> raw_func_name =
3401  module_object()->GetRawFunctionName(function_index());
3402  const int kMaxPrintedFunctionName = 64;
3403  char func_name[kMaxPrintedFunctionName + 1];
3404  int func_name_len = std::min(kMaxPrintedFunctionName, raw_func_name.length());
3405  memcpy(func_name, raw_func_name.begin(), func_name_len);
3406  func_name[func_name_len] = '\0';
3407  int pos = position();
3408  const wasm::WasmModule* module = trusted_instance_data()->module();
3409  int func_index = function_index();
3410  int func_code_offset = module->functions[func_index].code.offset();
3411  accumulator->Add(
3412  "], function #%u ('%s'), pc=%p (+0x%x), pos=%d (+%d) instance=%p\n",
3413  func_index, func_name, reinterpret_cast<void*>(pc()),
3414  static_cast<int>(pc() - instruction_start), pos, pos - func_code_offset,
3415  reinterpret_cast<void*>(trusted_instance_data()->ptr()));
3416  if (mode != OVERVIEW) accumulator->Add("\n");
3417 }

3465 
3466 FrameSummaries WasmFrame::Summarize() const {
3467  FrameSummaries summaries;
3468  // The {WasmCode*} escapes this scope via the {FrameSummary}, which is fine,
3469  // since this code object is part of our stack.
3470  wasm::WasmCode* code = wasm_code();
3471  int offset =
3472  static_cast<int>(maybe_unauthenticated_pc() - code->instruction_start());
3473  Handle<WasmTrustedInstanceData> instance_data{trusted_instance_data(),
3474  isolate()};
3475  // Push regular non-inlined summary.
3476  SourcePosition pos = code->GetSourcePositionBefore(offset);
3477  bool at_conversion = at_to_number_conversion();
3478  bool child_was_tail_call = false;
3479  // Add summaries for each inlined function at the current location.
3480  while (pos.isInlined()) {
3481  // Use current pc offset as the code offset for inlined functions.
3482  // This is not fully correct but there isn't a real code offset of a stack
3483  // frame for an inlined function as the inlined function is not a true
3484  // function with a defined start and end in the generated code.
3485  const auto [func_index, was_tail_call, caller_pos] =
3486  code->GetInliningPosition(pos.InliningId());
3487  if (!child_was_tail_call) {
3488  FrameSummary::WasmFrameSummary summary(isolate(), instance_data, code,
3489  pos.ScriptOffset(), func_index,
3490  at_conversion);
3491  summaries.frames.push_back(summary);
3492  }
3493  pos = caller_pos;
3494  at_conversion = false;
3495  child_was_tail_call = was_tail_call;
3496  }
3497 
3498  if (!child_was_tail_call) {
3499  int func_index = code->index();
3500  FrameSummary::WasmFrameSummary summary(isolate(), instance_data, code,
3501  pos.ScriptOffset(), func_index,
3502  at_conversion);
3503  summaries.frames.push_back(summary);
3504  }
3505 
3506  // The caller has to be on top.
3507  std::reverse(summaries.frames.begin(), summaries.frames.end());
3508  return summaries;
3509 }
3510 
3511 bool WasmFrame::at_to_number_conversion() const {
3512  if (callee_pc() == kNullAddress) return false;
3513  // Check whether our callee is a WASM_TO_JS frame, and this frame is at the
3514  // ToNumber conversion call.
3515  wasm::WasmCode* wasm_code =
3516  wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCode(isolate(), callee_pc());
3517 
3518  if (wasm_code) {
3519  if (wasm_code->kind() != wasm::WasmCode::kWasmToJsWrapper) return false;
3520  int offset = static_cast<int>(callee_pc() - wasm_code->instruction_start());
3521  int pos = wasm_code->GetSourceOffsetBefore(offset);
3522  // The imported call has position 0, ToNumber has position 1.
3523  // If there is no source position available, this is also not a ToNumber
3524  // call.
3525  DCHECK(pos == wasm::kNoCodePosition || pos == 0 || pos == 1);
3526  return pos == 1;
3527  }
3528 
3529  if (!IsWasmToJsWrapperCSA(callee_pc())) {
3530  return false;
3531  }
3532 
3533  // The generic wasm-to-js wrapper maintains a slot on the stack to indicate
3534  // its state. Initially this slot contains a pointer to the signature, so that
3535  // incoming parameters can be scanned. After all parameters have been
3536  // processed, this slot is reset to nullptr. After returning from JavaScript,
3537  // -1 is stored in the slot to indicate that any call from now on is a
3538  // ToNumber conversion.
3539  Address maybe_sig =
3540  Memory<Address>(callee_fp() + WasmToJSWrapperConstants::kSignatureOffset);
3541 
3542  return static_cast<intptr_t>(maybe_sig) == -1;
3543 }
3544 
3545 int WasmFrame::LookupExceptionHandlerInTable() {
3546  wasm::WasmCode* code =
3547  wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCode(isolate(), pc());
3548  if (!code->IsAnonymous() && code->handler_table_size() > 0) {
3549  HandlerTable table(code);
3550  int pc_offset = static_cast<int>(pc() - code->instruction_start());
3551  return table.LookupReturn(pc_offset);
3552  }
3553  return -1;
3554 }

3556 void WasmDebugBreakFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
3557  DCHECK(caller_pc());
3558  auto pair = wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCodeAndSafepoint(isolate(),
3559  caller_pc());
3560  SafepointEntry safepoint_entry = pair.second;
3561  uint32_t tagged_register_indexes = safepoint_entry.tagged_register_indexes();
3562 
3563  while (tagged_register_indexes != 0) {
3564  int reg_code = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros(tagged_register_indexes);
3565  tagged_register_indexes &= ~(1 << reg_code);
3566  FullObjectSlot spill_slot(&Memory<Address>(
3567  fp() +
3568  WasmDebugBreakFrameConstants::GetPushedGpRegisterOffset(reg_code)));
3569 
3570  v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, spill_slot);
3571  }
3572 }

3595 void JsToWasmFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
3596  // WrapperBuffer slot is RawPtr pointing to a stack.
3597  // Wasm instance and JS result array are passed as stack params.
3598  // So there is no need to visit them.
3599 
3600 #if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
3601  // Please reference GenericJSToWasmInterpreterWrapper for stack layout.
3602  if (v8_flags.wasm_jitless) {
3603  DCHECK(GetContainingCode(isolate(), pc()).value()->builtin_id() ==
3604  Builtin::kGenericJSToWasmInterpreterWrapper);
3605 
3606  // In a GenericJSToWasmInterpreterWrapper stack layout
3607  // ------+-----------------+----------------------
3608  // | return addr |
3609  // fp |- - - - - - - - -| -------------------|
3610  // | old fp | |
3611  // fp-p |- - - - - - - - -| |
3612  // | frame marker | | no GC scan
3613  // fp-2p |- - - - - - - - -| |
3614  // | scan_count | |
3615  // fp-3p |- - - - - - - - -| -------------------|
3616  // | .... | |
3617  // | .... | <- spill_slot_limit |
3618  // | spill slots | | GC scan scan_count slots
3619  // sp | .... | <- spill_slot_base--|
3620  // | | |
3621  // The [fp + BuiltinFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotCount] on the stack is a
3622  // value indicating how many values should be scanned from the top.
3623  intptr_t scan_count = *reinterpret_cast<intptr_t*>(
3624  fp() + BuiltinWasmInterpreterWrapperConstants::kGCScanSlotCountOffset);
3625 
3626  FullObjectSlot spill_slot_base(&Memory<Address>(sp()));
3627  FullObjectSlot spill_slot_limit(
3628  &Memory<Address>(sp() + scan_count * kSystemPointerSize));
3629  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, spill_slot_base,
3630  spill_slot_limit);
3631 
3632  // We should scan the arg/return values array which may hold heap pointers
3633  // for reference type of parameter/return values.
3634  uint32_t signature_data = *reinterpret_cast<uint32_t*>(
3635  fp() + BuiltinWasmInterpreterWrapperConstants::kSignatureDataOffset);
3636  bool has_ref_args =
3637  signature_data & wasm::WasmInterpreterRuntime::HasRefArgsField::kMask;
3638  bool has_ref_rets =
3639  signature_data & wasm::WasmInterpreterRuntime::HasRefRetsField::kMask;
3640 
3641  // This value indicates the array is currently used as args array. If false,
3642  // it's an array for return values.
3643  bool is_args = *reinterpret_cast<intptr_t*>(
3644  fp() + BuiltinWasmInterpreterWrapperConstants::kArgRetsIsArgsOffset);
3645  if ((is_args && !has_ref_args) || (!is_args && !has_ref_rets)) return;
3646 
3647  // Retrieve function signature.
3648  size_t return_count = *reinterpret_cast<size_t*>(
3649  fp() + BuiltinWasmInterpreterWrapperConstants::kReturnCountOffset);
3650  size_t param_count = *reinterpret_cast<size_t*>(
3651  fp() + BuiltinWasmInterpreterWrapperConstants::kParamCountOffset);
3652  const wasm::ValueType* reps = *reinterpret_cast<const wasm::ValueType**>(
3653  fp() + BuiltinWasmInterpreterWrapperConstants::kSigRepsOffset);
3654  wasm::FunctionSig sig(return_count, param_count, reps);
3655 
3656  intptr_t slot_ptr = *reinterpret_cast<intptr_t*>(
3657  fp() + BuiltinWasmInterpreterWrapperConstants::kArgRetsAddressOffset);
3658 
3659  if (is_args) {
3660  size_t current_index = *reinterpret_cast<size_t*>(
3661  fp() + BuiltinWasmInterpreterWrapperConstants::kCurrentIndexOffset);
3662  DCHECK_LE(current_index, param_count);
3663  for (size_t i = 0; i < current_index; i++) {
3664  wasm::ValueType type = sig.GetParam(i);
3665  if (type.is_reference()) {
3666  // Make sure slot for ref args are 64-bit aligned.
3667  slot_ptr += (slot_ptr & 0x04); // Branchless.
3668  FullObjectSlot array_slot(&Memory<Address>(slot_ptr));
3669  v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, array_slot);
3670  slot_ptr += kSystemPointerSize;
3671  } else {
3672  switch (type.kind()) {
3673  case wasm::kI32:
3674  case wasm::kF32:
3675  slot_ptr += sizeof(int32_t);
3676  break;
3677  case wasm::kI64:
3678  case wasm::kF64:
3679  slot_ptr += sizeof(int64_t);
3680  break;
3681  case wasm::kS128:
3682  default:
3683  UNREACHABLE();
3684  }
3685  }
3686  }
3687  } else {
3688  // When converting return values, all results are already in the array.
3689  for (size_t i = 0; i < return_count; i++) {
3690  wasm::ValueType type = sig.GetReturn(i);
3691  if (type.is_reference()) {
3692  // Make sure slot for ref args are 64-bit aligned.
3693  slot_ptr += (slot_ptr & 0x04); // Branchless.
3694  FullObjectSlot array_slot(&Memory<Address>(slot_ptr));
3695  v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, array_slot);
3696  slot_ptr += kSystemPointerSize;
3697  } else {
3698  switch (type.kind()) {
3699  case wasm::kI32:
3700  case wasm::kF32:
3701  slot_ptr += sizeof(int32_t);
3702  break;
3703  case wasm::kI64:
3704  case wasm::kF64:
3705  slot_ptr += sizeof(int64_t);
3706  break;
3707  case wasm::kS128:
3708  default:
3709  UNREACHABLE();
3710  }
3711  }
3712  }
3713  }
3714  }
3715 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
3716 }
3717 
3718 #if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
3719 void WasmToJsFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
3720  if (v8_flags.wasm_jitless) {
3721  // Called from GenericWasmToJSInterpreterWrapper.
3722  CHECK(v8_flags.jitless);
3723  // The [fp + BuiltinFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotLimit] on the stack is a
3724  // pointer to the end of the stack frame area that contains tagged objects.
3725  Address limit_sp = *reinterpret_cast<intptr_t*>(
3726  fp() + WasmToJSInterpreterFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotLimitOffset);
3727 
3728  FullObjectSlot spill_slot_base(&Memory<Address>(sp()));
3729  FullObjectSlot spill_slot_limit(limit_sp);
3730  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, spill_slot_base,
3731  spill_slot_limit);
3732  return;
3733  }
3734  WasmFrame::Iterate(v);
3735 }
3736 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE

3738 void StackSwitchFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
3739  // See JsToWasmFrame layout.
3740  // We cannot DCHECK that the pc matches the expected builtin code here,
3741  // because the return address is on a different stack.
3742  // The [fp + BuiltinFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotCountOffset] on the stack is a
3743  // value indicating how many values should be scanned from the top.
3744  intptr_t scan_count = Memory<intptr_t>(
3745  fp() + StackSwitchFrameConstants::kGCScanSlotCountOffset);
3746 
3747  FullObjectSlot spill_slot_base(&Memory<Address>(sp()));
3748  FullObjectSlot spill_slot_limit(
3749  &Memory<Address>(sp() + scan_count * kSystemPointerSize));
3750  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, spill_slot_base,
3751  spill_slot_limit);
3752  // Also visit fixed spill slots that contain references.
3753  FullObjectSlot instance_slot(
3754  &Memory<Address>(fp() + StackSwitchFrameConstants::kImplicitArgOffset));
3755  v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, instance_slot);
3756  FullObjectSlot result_array_slot(
3757  &Memory<Address>(fp() + StackSwitchFrameConstants::kResultArrayOffset));
3758  v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, result_array_slot);
3759 }

3761 #if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE
3762 void WasmInterpreterEntryFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
3763  // WasmInterpreterEntryFrame stack layout
3764  // ------+-----------------+----------------------
3765  // | return addr | |
3766  // fp |- - - - - - - - -| -------------------|
3767  // | prev fp | |
3768  // fp-p |- - - - - - - - -| | no GC scan
3769  // | frame marker | |
3770  // fp-2p |- - - - - - - - -| -------------------|-------------
3771  // | WasmInstanceObj | | GC scan
3772  // fp-3p |- - - - - - - - -| -------------------|-------------
3773  // | function_index | |
3774  // fp-4p |- - - - - - - - -| -------------------| no GC scan
3775  // | array_start | |
3776  // fp-5p |- - - - - - - - -| -------------------|
3777 
3778  static constexpr int kWasmInstanceObjOffset = -2 * kSystemPointerSize;
3779  FullObjectSlot slot_base(&Memory<Address>(fp() + kWasmInstanceObjOffset));
3780  FullObjectSlot slot_limit(
3781  &Memory<Address>(fp() + kWasmInstanceObjOffset + kSystemPointerSize));
3782  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, slot_base, slot_limit);
3783 }

3879 
3880 void WasmLiftoffSetupFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
3881  FullObjectSlot spilled_instance_slot(&Memory<Address>(
3882  fp() + WasmLiftoffSetupFrameConstants::kInstanceSpillOffset));
3883  v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, "spilled wasm instance",
3884  spilled_instance_slot);
3885  v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, "wasm instance data",
3886  wasm_instance_data_slot());
3887 
3888  wasm::NativeModule* native_module = GetNativeModule();
3889  int func_index = GetDeclaredFunctionIndex() +
3890  native_module->module()->num_imported_functions;
3891 
3892  // Scan the spill slots of the parameter registers. Parameters in WebAssembly
3893  // get reordered such that first all value parameters get put into registers.
3894  // If there are more registers than value parameters, the remaining registers
3895  // are used for reference parameters. Therefore we can determine which
3896  // registers get used for which parameters by counting the number of value
3897  // parameters and the number of reference parameters.
3898  int num_int_params = 0;
3899  int num_ref_params = 0;
3900  const wasm::FunctionSig* sig =
3901  native_module->module()->functions[func_index].sig;
3902  for (auto param : sig->parameters()) {
3903  if (param == wasm::kWasmI32) {
3904  num_int_params++;
3905  } else if (param == wasm::kWasmI64) {
3906  num_int_params += kSystemPointerSize == 8 ? 1 : 2;
3907  } else if (param.is_reference()) {
3908  num_ref_params++;
3909  }
3910  }
3911 
3912  // There are no reference parameters, there is nothing to scan.
3913  if (num_ref_params == 0) return;
3914 
3915  int num_int_params_in_registers =
3916  std::min(num_int_params,
3917  WasmLiftoffSetupFrameConstants::kNumberOfSavedGpParamRegs);
3918  int num_ref_params_in_registers =
3919  std::min(num_ref_params,
3920  WasmLiftoffSetupFrameConstants::kNumberOfSavedGpParamRegs -
3921  num_int_params_in_registers);
3922 
3923  for (int i = 0; i < num_ref_params_in_registers; ++i) {
3924  FullObjectSlot spill_slot(
3925  fp() + WasmLiftoffSetupFrameConstants::kParameterSpillsOffset
3926  [num_int_params_in_registers + i]);
3927 
3928  v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, "register parameter", spill_slot);
3929  }
3930 
3931  // Next we scan the slots of stack parameters.
3932  wasm::WasmCode* wasm_code = native_module->GetCode(func_index);
3933  uint32_t first_tagged_stack_slot = wasm_code->first_tagged_parameter_slot();
3934  uint32_t num_tagged_stack_slots = wasm_code->num_tagged_parameter_slots();
3935 
3936  // Visit tagged parameters that have been passed to the function of this
3937  // frame. Conceptionally these parameters belong to the parent frame.
3938  // However, the exact count is only known by this frame (in the presence of
3939  // tail calls, this information cannot be derived from the call site).
3940  if (num_tagged_stack_slots > 0) {
3941  FullObjectSlot tagged_parameter_base(&Memory<Address>(caller_sp()));
3942  tagged_parameter_base += first_tagged_stack_slot;
3943  FullObjectSlot tagged_parameter_limit =
3944  tagged_parameter_base + num_tagged_stack_slots;
3945 
3946  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, "stack parameter",
3947  tagged_parameter_base, tagged_parameter_limit);
3948  }
3949 }
3950 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY

3960  << "\n-----------------------------------------\n";

3962  }

3967 void JavaScriptFrame::Print(StringStream* accumulator, PrintMode mode,
3968  int index) const {
3969  DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared(function()->shared(), isolate());
3970  SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(isolate(), shared);
3971 
3972  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3973  Tagged<Object> receiver = this->receiver();
3974  Tagged<JSFunction> function = this->function();
3975 
3976  accumulator->PrintSecurityTokenIfChanged(isolate(), function);
3977  PrintIndex(accumulator, mode, index);
3978  PrintFrameKind(accumulator);
3979  if (IsConstructor()) accumulator->Add("new ");
3980  accumulator->PrintFunction(isolate(), function, receiver);
3981  accumulator->Add(" [%p]", function);
3982 
3983  // Get scope information for nicer output, if possible. If code is nullptr, or
3984  // doesn't contain scope info, scope_info will return 0 for the number of
3985  // parameters, stack local variables, context local variables, stack slots,
3986  // or context slots.
3987  Tagged<ScopeInfo> scope_info = shared->scope_info();
3988  Tagged<Object> script_obj = shared->script();
3989  if (IsScript(script_obj)) {
3990  Tagged<Script> script = Cast<Script>(script_obj);
3991  accumulator->Add(" [");
3992  accumulator->PrintName(script->name());
3993 
3994  if (is_interpreted()) {
3995  const InterpretedFrame* iframe = InterpretedFrame::cast(this);
3996  Tagged<BytecodeArray> bytecodes = iframe->GetBytecodeArray();
3997  int offset = iframe->GetBytecodeOffset();
3998  int source_pos = bytecodes->SourcePosition(offset);
3999  int line = script->GetLineNumber(source_pos) + 1;
4000  accumulator->Add(":%d] [bytecode=%p offset=%d]", line,
4001  reinterpret_cast<void*>(bytecodes.ptr()), offset);
4002  } else {
4003  int function_start_pos = shared->StartPosition();
4004  int line = script->GetLineNumber(function_start_pos) + 1;
4005  accumulator->Add(":~%d] [pc=%p]", line, reinterpret_cast<void*>(pc()));
4006  }
4007  }
4008 
4009  accumulator->Add("(this=%o", receiver);
4010 
4011  // Print the parameters.
4012  int parameters_count = ComputeParametersCount();
4013  for (int i = 0; i < parameters_count; i++) {
4014  accumulator->Add(",");
4015  accumulator->Add("%o", GetParameter(i));
4016  }
4017 
4018  accumulator->Add(")");
4019  if (mode == OVERVIEW) {
4020  accumulator->Add("\n");
4021  return;
4022  }
4023  if (is_optimized()) {
4024  accumulator->Add(" {\n// optimized frame\n");
4025  PrintFunctionSource(accumulator, *shared);
4026  accumulator->Add("}\n");
4027  return;
4028  }
4029  accumulator->Add(" {\n");
4030 
4031  // Compute the number of locals and expression stack elements.
4032  int heap_locals_count = scope_info->ContextLocalCount();
4033  int expressions_count = ComputeExpressionsCount();
4034 
4035  // Try to get hold of the context of this frame.
4036  Tagged<Context> context;
4037  if (IsContext(this->context())) {
4038  context = Cast<Context>(this->context());
4039  while (context->IsWithContext()) {
4040  context = context->previous();
4041  DCHECK(!context.is_null());
4042  }
4043  }
4044 
4045  // Print heap-allocated local variables.
4046  if (heap_locals_count > 0) {
4047  accumulator->Add(" // heap-allocated locals\n");
4048  }
4049  for (auto it : ScopeInfo::IterateLocalNames(scope_info, no_gc)) {
4050  accumulator->Add(" var ");
4051  accumulator->PrintName(it->name());
4052  accumulator->Add(" = ");
4053  if (!context.is_null()) {
4054  int slot_index = Context::MIN_CONTEXT_SLOTS + it->index();
4055  if (slot_index < context->length()) {
4056  accumulator->Add("%o", context->get(slot_index, kRelaxedLoad));
4057  } else {
4058  accumulator->Add(
4059  "// warning: missing context slot - inconsistent frame?");
4060  }
4061  } else {
4062  accumulator->Add("// warning: no context found - inconsistent frame?");
4063  }
4064  accumulator->Add("\n");
4065  }
4066 
4067  // Print the expression stack.
4068  if (0 < expressions_count) {
4069  accumulator->Add(" // expression stack (top to bottom)\n");
4070  }
4071  for (int i = expressions_count - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
4072  accumulator->Add(" [%02d] : %o\n", i, GetExpression(i));
4073  }
4074 
4075  PrintFunctionSource(accumulator, *shared);
4076 
4077  accumulator->Add("}\n\n");
4078 }

4084 void CommonFrame::IterateExpressions(RootVisitor* v) const {
4085  const int last_object_offset = StandardFrameConstants::kLastObjectOffset;
4086  intptr_t marker =
4087  Memory<intptr_t>(fp() + CommonFrameConstants::kContextOrFrameTypeOffset);
4088  FullObjectSlot base(&Memory<Address>(sp()));
4089  FullObjectSlot limit(&Memory<Address>(fp() + last_object_offset) + 1);
4090  CHECK(StackFrame::IsTypeMarker(marker));
4091  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, base, limit);
4092 }

4094 void JavaScriptFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
4095  // The frame contains the actual argument count (intptr) that should not be
4096  // visited.
4097  FullObjectSlot argc(
4098  &Memory<Address>(fp() + StandardFrameConstants::kArgCOffset));
4099  const int last_object_offset = StandardFrameConstants::kLastObjectOffset;
4100  FullObjectSlot base(&Memory<Address>(sp()));
4101  FullObjectSlot limit(&Memory<Address>(fp() + last_object_offset) + 1);
4102  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, base, argc);
4103  v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, argc + 1, limit);
4104  IteratePc(v, constant_pool_address(), GcSafeLookupCode());
4105 }
4106 
4107 void InternalFrame::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) const {
4108  Tagged<GcSafeCode> code = GcSafeLookupCode();
4109  IteratePc(v, constant_pool_address(), code);
4110  // Internal frames typically do not receive any arguments, hence their stack
4111  // only contains tagged pointers.
4112  // We are misusing the has_tagged_outgoing_params flag here to tell us whether
4113  // the full stack frame contains only tagged pointers or only raw values.
4114  // This is used for the WasmCompileLazy builtin, where we actually pass
4115  // untagged arguments and also store untagged values on the stack.
4116  if (code->has_tagged_outgoing_params()) IterateExpressions(v);
4117 }

4123 // Predictably converts PC to uint32 by calculating offset of the PC in
4124 // from the embedded builtins start or from respective MemoryChunk.
4125 uint32_t PcAddressForHashing(Isolate* isolate, Address address) {
4126  uint32_t hashable_address;
4127  if (OffHeapInstructionStream::TryGetAddressForHashing(isolate, address,
4128  &hashable_address)) {
4129  return hashable_address;
4130  }
4131  return ObjectAddressForHashing(address);
4132 }

4136 InnerPointerToCodeCache::InnerPointerToCodeCacheEntry*
4137 InnerPointerToCodeCache::GetCacheEntry(Address inner_pointer) {
4138  DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(kInnerPointerToCodeCacheSize));
4139  uint32_t hash =
4140  ComputeUnseededHash(PcAddressForHashing(isolate_, inner_pointer));
4141  uint32_t index = hash & (kInnerPointerToCodeCacheSize - 1);
4142  InnerPointerToCodeCacheEntry* entry = cache(index);
4143  if (entry->inner_pointer == inner_pointer) {
4144  // Why this DCHECK holds is nontrivial:
4145  //
4146  // - the cache is filled lazily on calls to this function.
4147  // - this function may be called while GC, and in particular
4148  // MarkCompactCollector::UpdatePointersAfterEvacuation, is in progress.
4149  // - the cache is cleared at the end of UpdatePointersAfterEvacuation.
4150  // - now, why does pointer equality hold even during moving GC?
4151  // - .. because GcSafeFindCodeForInnerPointer does not follow forwarding
4152  // pointers and always returns the old object (which is still valid,
4153  // *except* for the map_word).
4154  DCHECK_EQ(entry->code,
4155  isolate_->heap()->GcSafeFindCodeForInnerPointer(inner_pointer));
4156  } else {
4157  // Because this code may be interrupted by a profiling signal that
4158  // also queries the cache, we cannot update inner_pointer before the code
4159  // has been set. Otherwise, we risk trying to use a cache entry before
4160  // the code has been computed.
4161  entry->code =
4162  isolate_->heap()->GcSafeFindCodeForInnerPointer(inner_pointer);
4163  if (entry->code.value()->is_maglevved()) {
4164  entry->maglev_safepoint_entry.Reset();
4165  } else {
4166  entry->safepoint_entry.Reset();
4167  }
4168  entry->inner_pointer = inner_pointer;
4169  }
4170  return entry;
4171 }

4184 bool BuiltinContinuationModeIsWithCatch(BuiltinContinuationMode mode) {
4185  switch (mode) {
4186  case BuiltinContinuationMode::STUB:
4187  case BuiltinContinuationMode::JAVASCRIPT:
4188  return false;
4189  case BuiltinContinuationMode::JAVASCRIPT_WITH_CATCH:
4190  case BuiltinContinuationMode::JAVASCRIPT_HANDLE_EXCEPTION:
4191  return true;
4192  }

4198 UnoptimizedFrameInfo::UnoptimizedFrameInfo(int parameters_count_with_receiver,
4199  int translation_height,
4200  bool is_topmost, bool pad_arguments,
4201  FrameInfoKind frame_info_kind) {
4202  const int locals_count = translation_height;
4203 
4204  register_stack_slot_count_ =
4205  UnoptimizedFrameConstants::RegisterStackSlotCount(locals_count);
4206 
4207  static constexpr int kTheAccumulator = 1;
4208  static constexpr int kTopOfStackPadding = TopOfStackRegisterPaddingSlots();
4209  int maybe_additional_slots =
4210  (is_topmost || frame_info_kind == FrameInfoKind::kConservative)
4211  ? (kTheAccumulator + kTopOfStackPadding)
4212  : 0;
4213  frame_size_in_bytes_without_fixed_ =
4214  (register_stack_slot_count_ + maybe_additional_slots) *
4215  kSystemPointerSize;
4216 
4217  // The 'fixed' part of the frame consists of the incoming parameters and
4218  // the part described by InterpreterFrameConstants. This will include
4219  // argument padding, when needed.
4220  const int parameter_padding_slots =
4221  pad_arguments ? ArgumentPaddingSlots(parameters_count_with_receiver) : 0;
4222  const int fixed_frame_size =
4223  InterpreterFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSize +
4224  (parameters_count_with_receiver + parameter_padding_slots) *
4225  kSystemPointerSize;
4226  frame_size_in_bytes_ = frame_size_in_bytes_without_fixed_ + fixed_frame_size;
4227 }
4228 
4229 // static
4230 uint32_t UnoptimizedFrameInfo::GetStackSizeForAdditionalArguments(
4231  int parameters_count) {
4232  return (parameters_count + ArgumentPaddingSlots(parameters_count)) *
4233  kSystemPointerSize;
4234 }

4236 ConstructStubFrameInfo::ConstructStubFrameInfo(int translation_height,
4237  bool is_topmost,
4238  FrameInfoKind frame_info_kind) {
4239  // Note: This is according to the Translation's notion of 'parameters' which
4240  // differs to that of the SharedFunctionInfo, e.g. by including the receiver.
4241  const int parameters_count = translation_height;
4242 
4243  // If the construct frame appears to be topmost we should ensure that the
4244  // value of result register is preserved during continuation execution.
4245  // We do this here by "pushing" the result of the constructor function to
4246  // the top of the reconstructed stack and popping it in
4247  // {Builtin::kNotifyDeoptimized}.
4248 
4249  static constexpr int kTopOfStackPadding = TopOfStackRegisterPaddingSlots();
4250  static constexpr int kTheResult = 1;
4251  const int argument_padding = ArgumentPaddingSlots(parameters_count);
4252 
4253  const int adjusted_height =
4254  (is_topmost || frame_info_kind == FrameInfoKind::kConservative)
4255  ? parameters_count + argument_padding + kTheResult +
4256  kTopOfStackPadding
4257  : parameters_count + argument_padding;
4258  frame_size_in_bytes_without_fixed_ = adjusted_height * kSystemPointerSize;
4259  frame_size_in_bytes_ = frame_size_in_bytes_without_fixed_ +
4260  ConstructFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSize;
4261 }
4262 
4263 FastConstructStubFrameInfo::FastConstructStubFrameInfo(bool is_topmost) {
4264  // If the construct frame appears to be topmost we should ensure that the
4265  // value of result register is preserved during continuation execution.
4266  // We do this here by "pushing" the result of the constructor function to
4267  // the top of the reconstructed stack and popping it in
4268  // {Builtin::kNotifyDeoptimized}.
4269 
4270  static constexpr int kTopOfStackPadding = TopOfStackRegisterPaddingSlots();
4271  static constexpr int kTheResult = 1;
4272  const int adjusted_height =
4273  ArgumentPaddingSlots(1) +
4274  (is_topmost ? kTheResult + kTopOfStackPadding : 0);
4275  frame_size_in_bytes_without_fixed_ = adjusted_height * kSystemPointerSize;
4276  frame_size_in_bytes_ = frame_size_in_bytes_without_fixed_ +
4277  FastConstructFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSize;

4280 BuiltinContinuationFrameInfo::BuiltinContinuationFrameInfo(
4281  int translation_height,
4282  const CallInterfaceDescriptor& continuation_descriptor,
4283  const RegisterConfiguration* register_config, bool is_topmost,
4284  DeoptimizeKind deopt_kind, BuiltinContinuationMode continuation_mode,
4285  FrameInfoKind frame_info_kind) {
4286  const bool is_conservative = frame_info_kind == FrameInfoKind::kConservative;
4287 
4288  // Note: This is according to the Translation's notion of 'parameters' which
4289  // differs to that of the SharedFunctionInfo, e.g. by including the receiver.
4290  const int parameters_count = translation_height;
4291  frame_has_result_stack_slot_ =
4292  !is_topmost || deopt_kind == DeoptimizeKind::kLazy;
4293  const int result_slot_count =
4294  (frame_has_result_stack_slot_ || is_conservative) ? 1 : 0;
4295 
4296  const int exception_slot_count =
4297  (BuiltinContinuationModeIsWithCatch(continuation_mode) || is_conservative)
4298  ? 1
4299  : 0;
4300 
4301  const int allocatable_register_count =
4302  register_config->num_allocatable_general_registers();
4303  const int padding_slot_count =
4304  BuiltinContinuationFrameConstants::PaddingSlotCount(
4305  allocatable_register_count);
4306 
4307  const int register_parameter_count =
4308  continuation_descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount();
4309  translated_stack_parameter_count_ =
4310  parameters_count - register_parameter_count;
4311  stack_parameter_count_ = translated_stack_parameter_count_ +
4312  result_slot_count + exception_slot_count;
4313  const int stack_param_pad_count =
4314  ArgumentPaddingSlots(stack_parameter_count_);
4315 
4316  // If the builtins frame appears to be topmost we should ensure that the
4317  // value of result register is preserved during continuation execution.
4318  // We do this here by "pushing" the result of callback function to the
4319  // top of the reconstructed stack and popping it in
4320  // {Builtin::kNotifyDeoptimized}.
4321  static constexpr int kTopOfStackPadding = TopOfStackRegisterPaddingSlots();
4322  static constexpr int kTheResult = 1;
4323  const int push_result_count =
4324  (is_topmost || is_conservative) ? kTheResult + kTopOfStackPadding : 0;
4325 
4326  frame_size_in_bytes_ =
4327  kSystemPointerSize * (stack_parameter_count_ + stack_param_pad_count +
4328  allocatable_register_count + padding_slot_count +
4329  push_result_count) +
4330  BuiltinContinuationFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSize;
4331 
4332  frame_size_in_bytes_above_fp_ =
4333  kSystemPointerSize * (allocatable_register_count + padding_slot_count +
4334  push_result_count) +
4335  (BuiltinContinuationFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSize -
4336  BuiltinContinuationFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp);
4337 }
